Commentary.Commentary: It is time for the West Indies to start their first innings now. The Bangladesh players are in a huddle and they disperse now to take their respective positions. Kraigg Brathwaite and John Campbell are the openers for West Indies. Shoriful Islam has a brand new Dukes ball in his hand. Here we go...
.... Second Innings ...

If we ignore the variable bounce, it appears to be a great batting strip. Bangladesh have wasted a good chance to put a massive total on the board and will have to make use of the new ball to pick early wickets. Let's see how things pan out in the remaining part of the day's play. Stay tuned...

It was hard work for West Indies in the first session on a pitch that had the reputation of being juicy for the pacers. There wasn't too much help for them, but through disciplined and consistent lines, the hosts started to create inroads in the afternoon session and extended the good work after Tea. Alzarri Joseph and Jayden Seales picked up three wickets apiece and were the most successful bowlers whereas debutant Anderson Phillip also bagged a couple of wickets. Kemar Roach had an off day and remained wicket-less, and he also was taken for aplenty by the lower order of Bangladesh.

Some crucial runs from the Bangladesh tail, and the tourists have ended up with a decent total in the first innings. If you consider their batting effort in Antigua, this certainly is a much-improved performance. That said, after the kind of courage they showed in the morning session, it's disappointing that they got bundled out in the evening session itself. Litton Das stood out with the bat, along with Tamim Iqbal, and there were starts for a few batters as well, but the wickets fell at regular intervals to hamper their progress.

OUT! CAUGHT! That's it, Bangladesh have been bowled out for 234! Seales bowls a short ball, probably the best ball to bowl to a tailender. It is angled on the body and Khaled Ahmed has no idea what to do with it. He ends up just hanging his bat in front of his body and gets a thick outside edge. The ball loops up in the air towards gully and Nkrumah Bonner there takes an easy catch.
Commentary.Howout: c Nkrumah Bonner b Jayden Seales

Commentary.Commentary: Shortish length, around off. Khaled Ahmed blocks it out.
Back of a length, around off. Ebadot Hossain defends it towards the off side.
A short ball on off. Ebadot Hossain ducks under it.
Keeps it a tad short, around off. Ebadot Hossain pushes at it but gets a thick outside edge. The ball runs through the gully region and the batters run two.
Back of a length, around off. Ebadot Hossain defends it square of the wicket on the off side.
Shortish length and outside off. Ebadot Hossain looks to push at it but gets beaten.
Back of a length, on leg. Khaled Ahmed clips it towards fine leg for a single.
Length delivery, around off. Khaled Ahmed defends it towards the off side.
Back of a length, on off. Khaled Ahmed blocks it out.
FOUR! Now, Khaled Ahmed gets off the mark with a boundary! Drifting on the pads. Ahmed just clips it towards the fine leg fence for a boundary.
Khaled Ahmed is the number 11 batter.

OUT! CAUGHT! Finally, West Indies manage to break this partnership and Shoriful Islam departs after playing a handy cameo here! Shoriful Islam backs away a bit early and Seales follows him and bowls a full ball on his legs. Islam flicks it aerially towards deep square leg and Jermaine Blackwood running to his left takes a fine low catch. Important wicket, West Indies needed this badly!
Commentary.Howout: c Jermaine Blackwood b Jayden Seales

Commentary.Commentary: Back of a length, around off. Islam swings but misses.

Goes short on middle. Shoriful Islam makes room and looks to pull it. However, he gets a top edge and it is Devon Thomas again who runs to his left from fine leg and dives to stop it near the fence. Two runs are taken.
This is very full on off. Ebadot Hossain blocks it out.
Kemar Roach is removed from the attack. In comes Jayden Seales...
Goes fuller on middle. Ebadot Hossain drives it to mid on.
Lands on a length, on off again. Ebadot Hossain manages to negate it again.
On a length, around off. Ebadot Hossain defends it towards the off side.
On a length, around off. Ebadot Hossain guides it through the backward point region for a couple. He opened his bat-face nicely there.
A fullish delivery and down the leg side. Ebadot Hossain looks to clip it but misses.

FOUR! The frustration continues for West Indies! Fullish delivery on middle and leg. Shoriful Islam backs away again and swings wildly. He gets an inside edge and the ball goes past stumps to run away for another boundary at fine leg. This is now Shoriful Islam's best Test score.
Goes fuller on off. Islam drills it to deep cover for a couple this time.

FOUR! Another boundary for Shoriful Islam and these are crucial runs for Bangladesh. It is full and around off. Islam makes room and just throws his bat it. The ball goes off the outside half of his blade towards the backward point fence for a boundary.
Roach angles another short ball on middle and leg. Islam ducks under it.
Again a short delivery on off. Islam tries to pull it but misses.
Roach bangs it short around off. Shoriful Islam backs away and swings across the line but misses.

EDGY FOUR! Fuller in length and outside off, Ebadot leans forward to drive and edges it behind. It flies through the vacant third slip region for a boundary. This stand moves to 22 and continues to frustrate West Indies.
Around off, on a length and there is some extra bounce, the batter goes on his toes and defends it down.
On a length and around off, Ebadot stays back and pushes it defensively to point.
Shortish and around off, defended from the back foot to covers.
Joseph goes full and around leg, Shoriful tries to flick but misses. It goes off his pads to short fine leg and they cross for a leg bye. Also, the bowler has overstepped.
Shortish and angling down the leg side, Ebadot helps it down to fine leg for a run. Roach fumbles slightly and Ebadot turns for the second run but he is sent back.
Back of a length, just outside off and shaping in, Ebadot pokes at it and gets beaten on the inside edge.
Swing and a miss! Short in length and on off, at 127 kph, Islam swings his bat early at it and misses.

FOUR! Three boundaries in the over and this is turning out to be a handy cameo from Shoriful. He is anticipating the short deliveries well. Hangs back on the back foot and powers it over mid on for a boundary.
Short ball on off, at 132 kph, Shoriful tries to sway away but gets hit on the right arm.
FOUR! Boom! 200 comes up for Bangladesh. Back of a length, around off, Shoriful hangs on the back foot and whacks it through wide mid off for a boundary.

FOUR! Not where the batter intended to hit. Short and outside off, Shoriful tries to pull but ends up flat-batting it unintentionally past point for a boundary. Roach smiles, his search for the 250th Test wicket continues.
Roach delivers it from wide of the crease, on a length around middle, Ebadot shuffles across and nudges it to fine leg for a run.
Fuller in length and outside off, Islam drives it through covers for two.
Short and outside off, Shoriful flashes his bat at it but fails to connect.
Shoriful Islam is the next man in.

OUT! CAUGHT! Litton Das stands there in disbelief. A touch short in length, around off at 131 kph, Das stays back and tries to pull but does so aerially and to the right of mid on. Kraigg Brathwaite takes a sharp catch and Joseph has three wickets now. A handy knock from Litton Das comes to an end but his team wanted more from him. Bangladesh are 9 away from touching 200. Can they?
Commentary.Howout: c Kraigg Brathwaite b Alzarri Joseph

Commentary.Commentary: Bangs in a short ball around off, Das ducks and the keeper jumps to collect the ball.
Fuller in length, around off, Das closes the face of his bat and helps it to mid-wicket.
Starts with a full delivery down the leg side, Litton tries to flick but misses.
Alzarri Joseph (11-1-37-2) is back into the attack now.
Shortish and on off, nicely defended from the back foot by Ebadot.
Back of a length again, around leg, Ebadot glances it to deep backward square leg and calls for two. Gets two. Gaining in confidence, the number 9.
Shortish and on off, Ebadot defends it safely from the back foot.
Bumper around leg, Ebadot tries to repeat the last shot but misses. There is a leg gully in place now.
FOUR! These are frustrating runs for West Indies. Back of a length, around middle and leg, Ebadot nudges it to fine leg and it scoots away to the fence.
Bouncer, around middle and leg, Ebadot Hossain ducks.

FOUR! Put away in style! Fifty for Litton, his 14th in Tests. Fuller in length, around middle and leg, Das picks it up off his pads and whips it to the deep mid-wicket fence. Now, Ebadot Hossain will be on strike for the start of the next over.

Miscalculation perhaps. Full and outside off, Ebadot strokes it in the gap at covers and they think about two. Only one is available and Litton is back on strike. Will he eye a single or look for a boundary?
Around off, on a length, Das pushes it towards wide mid off and scampers across to the other end. Again two balls to survive for Ebadot.
Fuller in length and angling down the leg side, Das fails to flick and it goes off his pads to fine leg. Roach makes the stop and they collect two leg byes.

FOUR! Cracking shot! Seales digs it in again, short and around off, Litton rides the bounce and hammer-pulls it in front of square on the leg side. There is a fielder in the deep but he fails to cut it off.
Short in length, around leg, Das tries to pull but fails to connect.
Play and a miss! Shortish delivery, outside off, Ebadot goes hunting for the line as he wants to defend. Nearly edges it behind. He is disappointed with himself.
Bouncer around middle and leg, easily ducked by Ebadot.
Delivers it on a length and outside off, Das pushes it with an angled bat through point for one. Two balls to survive for Ebadot.
Full and outside off, Das gets on the front foot and defends it with gentle hands towards gully.
On a length around off, defended to covers.
Short and wide outside off, Das camps back and whacks it to the right of the deep point fielder. He collects a couple.
A touch short in length and outside off, Ebadot initially looks to feel for it but then withdraws his bat.
Edged but safe! Back of a length, around off, Ebadot tries to defend from the crease but gets an outside edge. It falls in front of Mayers at second slip.
Bouncer outside off, Ebadot takes evasive action and ducks immediately.
On a length, around middle, it's nudged down to fine leg for one.

FOUR! Controlled shot! Short in length and wide outside off, Das chases it and guides it by opening the face of his bat. He places it wide of the gully fielder for a boundary. His presence is the key if Bangladesh have to touch 200, at least.
The batter has just watchfully blocked this out.
Fires in a length ball on off, Ebadot Hossain defends it back.
A bouncer to greet the new batter, Ebadot Hossain leaps and evades it.
Ebadot Hossain walks out to the middle.

OUT! That's a stunning catch from Devon Thomas, the substitute fielder. Kyle Mayers keeps feeding short delivery outside off to Mehidy Hasan who doesn't back down and attempts to crack it over point once more. This time though the connection is not accurate as it flies from the higher part of his bat. Devon Thomas runs across a bit to his left from backward point and then puts in a full-length dive to take a ripper. Kyle Mayers continues to provide breakthroughs to his team with his dibbly-dobblies.
Commentary.Howout: c sub Devon Thomas b Kyle Mayers

Commentary.Commentary: Shortish and on off, punched off the outside half to gully.
FOUR! That region is left open for Mehidy Hasan. Short and outside off, Mehidy Hasan cracks it through backward point for a boundary.
Short and wide outside off, Das steers it to deep point for a single. West Indies have plugged that productive region for Litton.
Kyle Mayers to start from the other end.
Fuller in length and outside off, driven to covers.
Around off, on a length, that is defended solidly off the front foot.
Short and on off, Das pulls it awkwardly to deep mid-wicket for one.
Back of a length, around off, defended to the off side.

Misunderstanding but no harm is done. Jayden Seales darts in a length ball on off, staying low, Das keeps it out to cover-point and looks for a run. He is sent back as Raymon Reifer misses his shy at the striker's end. The ball travels to square leg and again Litton comes out in search of a run. Mehidy Hasan is going nowhere and Das has to return.
Starts by angling in a length ball around off, Litton Das is forward with a straight blade in defense.

Welcome back, folks! We are all set for the final session of Day 1. The West Indian players make their way out to the middle and the two Bangladesh batters, Litton Das and Mehidy Hasan are also back to resume their innings. Jayden Seales will start the proceedings after Tea. Here we go...
… DAY 1, SESSION 3 …

The afternoon session belonged to West Indies! With the pitch offering very little assistance to the bowlers, the hosts resorted to disciplined lines and reaped rich rewards. They got lucky with two umpire's call going their way, and a couple more came their way courtesy of some accurate and sharp bowling. Bangladesh have lost the small advantage gained in the morning session and would be aiming to wrestle back some control in the final session. Litton Das has looked in control during his stay and a big responsibility lies on his shoulders to bat with the lower order and take the visitors towards a decent total. Do join us at 12.30 am IST (7 pm GMT, the previous day) for the remainder of Day1.
Back of a length, around off. Mehidy Hasan rides the bounce and defends it square off the wicket on the off side. At Tea on Day 1, Bangladesh are 159/6!
Goes fuller on middle and leg. Mehidy Hasan clips it to square leg.
Short and outside off, played down to point for a run.
Lands on a length, on off. Das blocks it solidly off the back foot.
Full and outside off, played past gully for two.
A touch short and outside off, shaping in, Das tries to cut but gets too close to the delivery. He is hit on the gloves.
Kyle Mayers to bowl the final over before Tea. 5-0-24-1 are his figures so far.
On a length and outside off. Mehidy Hasan leaves it alone.
Anderson Phillip is leaving the field. Devon Thomas is the substitute now.

FOUR! Anderson Phillip with a misfield and that gives Mehidy Hasan a boundary! Overpitched on off. Mehidy Hasan drives it towards the cover fieldeer. However, the ball goes through Anderson Phillip who is late to get down and it races away towards the fence.
On a length angling into off. Mehidy Hasan makes a solid block again.
Continues with that shortish length, on off and Mehidy Hasan defends it nicely, right under his eyes.
On a length, outside off. Das punches it through covers for a single.
Shortish length, on off. Das blocks it off the back foot.

That's a risky shot on the pitch that has shown some extra bounce every now and then. Back of a length, around off. Mehidy Hasan looks to punch it off the back foot but gets the inside half of his blade and the ball rolls towards the leg side.
Seales with a good bouncer angling into off. Mehidy Hasan though is quite alert and ducks under it.
On a length, on off. Mehidy Hasan blocks it from his crease.
Goes a tad fuller and outside off. Hasan presses forward to defend but gets a thick outside edge that rolls away towards the fourth slip fielder.
Seales angles this length delivery on middle and leg. Das nudges it to fine leg for a single.
On a length, on off. Das blocks it out.
On a length, and around off. Mehidy Hasan makes a good leave.
Lovely delivery! Alzarri Joseph goes full and outside off. It shapes away nicely and beats the outside edge of Hasan's blade who looks to drive it away.
Angling into middle, on a length again. Mehidy Hasan defends it towards the leg side.
Nicely bowled! Lands on a good length, around off. Mehidy Hasan looks to defend it but the ball nips away and beats the outside edge of the batter's blade.
Back of a length, outside off. Mehidy Hasan leaves it alone.
A short delivery on off. Das pulls it to deep square leg for a single.
Serves a length delivery on off. Mehidy Hasan with a solid block back to the bowler.
Lands on a length, outside off. Mehidy Hasan leaves it alone.
Seales keeps it a tad short again angling into the body of the batter. Mehidy Hasan works it just short of the fine leg fielder.
On a length, outside off. Mehidy Hasan leaves it alone.
Back of a length, on off. This time Mehidy Hasan is right behind it and blocks it out.
Seales starts the new spell with a short delivery, around off. Hasan lets it go.
Bowling change. Jayden Seales to have another spell. 1 for 30 in his 8 overs so far.
Shortish length again, outside off. Litton Das punches it through covers this time and comes back for the second run.

FOUR! Another eye-catching shot from the talented Litton Das! It is slightly shorter in length and outside off. Das rides the bounce nicely and punches it through backward point for a lovely boundary.
That nips back in sharply! Lands on a length, around off and it comes back into Das. He looks to push it away but gets hit high on his pads.
Back of a length, outside off. Das leaves it alone.
Joseph goes fuller on leg. Hasan clips it to fine leg for a single.
Alzarri Joseph bangs it short on middle. Mehidy Hasan ducks under it.
A full delivery on off. Das drives it to mid off. Nicely timed but straight to the fielder.
Beaten! Roach hits the length hard, around off. Das goes pushing for it but the ball seams away a bit and beats the outside edge of his blade.
Roach goes full again but the line is much straighter. Das drives it to mid on.
FOUR! Confident shot from Das! Overpitched, around off. Das drives and drives it crisply in the gap through covers for a boundary.
Goes fuller on off. Das drives it to the cover fielder.
On a length, on off. Das blocks it off the front foot.
Back of a length, outside off and Mehidy Hasan leaves it again.
A short delivery, around off. Mehidy Hasan leaves it alone.
Mehidy Hasan is the new batter.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! The short stuff works for Alzarri Joseph and West Indies, and Bangladesh lose another. They are losing their way here and West Indies will be pretty happy with their effort so far post-Lunch. Joseph bangs it short again and this time at an awkward height for Hasan angling into the body. Hasan tries to sway away from the line of the ball first and then just tries to fend it away. However, he ends up getting only his gloves on this one and the ball loops up in the air towards the keeper, Joshua Da Silva. He backtracks to take an easy catch and Hasan walks back disappointed after consulting his partner regarding unlocking the DRS. The replays show that Nurul Hasan was trying to fox the umpire by rubbing his shoulder but umpire Joel Wilson has watched everything clearly and knows these tricks of the batters.
Commentary.Howout: c Joshua Da Silva b Alzarri Joseph

Commentary.Commentary: Good short delivery angling into middle. Hasan ducks under it and Joshua Da Silva does well to stop it with a jump.
Goes a tad fuller on middle. Das works it to fine leg for a single.
Back of a length, on off. Das tries to defend it but the ball bounces a bit more and hits him high on his pads.
Change in bowling. Alzarri Joseph is back for another burst. 7-1-23-1 are his figures thus far.
Roach delivers it on a length, on off. Hasan defends it out watchfully.
Continues to pitch it on a good length, on off. Hasan with a defensive block again.
Serves a length delivery, a tad outside off and Hasan defends it off the front foot.
Goes fuller, on middle. Hasan drives it to mid on.
On a length, on off. Hasan blocks it out.
On a length, on off. Hasan defends it off the front foot towards the off side.
Back of a length, on off. Das blocks it out solidly.
On a length, around off. Das looks to defend it but the ball seams away a bit and beats the outside edge of his blade.
Shortish-length delivery, on off. Das rides the bounce and punches it towards covers.
Lands on a length and outside off. Das leaves it alone.
On a length, on off. Das blocks it out.

Extra bounce from this end as Anderson Phillip bowls it back of a length, around off. Das looks to defend but gets surprised by the bounce and the ball hits him high on his blade. Good thing was that he played it with soft hands, so the ball falls short of the third slip fielder.
Serves a length delivery again and comes back to his line, around off. Hasan defends it watchfully.
Roach with another length delivery but it is outside off. Hasan cuts it but finds the point fielder.
Keeps it on a length, around off. Hasan defends it solidly towards the off side.
Back of a length, on off. Hasan blocks it off the back foot.
On a length and around off. Hasan looks to defend but gets an inside edge onto his pads.

Ohh...low bounce there! Actually, Nurul Hasan does well to get his bat down in time. On a length, angling into off. It stays quite low than the batter can expect from that length and Hasan in the end manages to defend it.
Kemar Roach (9-1-24-0) is back on.
Turns a length ball wide of mid on and crosses for a run.
Short and on middle, helped down to fine leg for one.
Around off, on a length and angling in, Das gets forward and blocks.
On a length, around off, defended.
Shortish and on off, punched from the back foot to the off side.
Angles in a length ball on middle, Hasan works it behind square leg and picks up a single.

FOUR! Glorious! Back of a length and outside off, Litton plays it square of the wicket on the off side, controls his shot well and offers an angled bat to beat the point fielder. He loves playing there. Sublime.
That is defended off the back foot to the off side for a single.
FOUR! Fine shot to open your account. Short again from Seales, wide outside off, Nurul Hasan climbs onto it and whacks it through backward point for a boundary.
Shortish and outside off, Nurul is on the back foot as he plays it down to point.
Nurul Hasan is the next man in.

OUT! DRAGS IT ON! Playing away from the body has eventually brought Shakib's downfall. Jayden Seales puts a harmless shortish delivery outside off, at 132 clicks, Shakib Al Hasan attempts to punch it away from the body but all he manages is an inside edge onto the stumps. Seales looks at the heavens in delight as a disappointed Shakib Al Hasan returns to the pavilion. Bangladesh are going downhill rapidly.
Commentary.Howout: b Jayden Seales

Commentary.Commentary: Angles in a shortish ball on off, Shakib defends it from the back foot.

DRINKS! West Indies have done well to take two wickets in this first hour after Lunch and the pressure is now back on Bangladesh. The tourists have been good with the bat so far but they would like this pair of Litton Das and Shakib Al Hasan to bat long here. The pitch is not as pacer-friendly as everyone expected it to be at the start of this game and one feels that a good first innings total will be a crucial factor for Bangladesh. West Indies, on the other hand, would know that they just need to bowl with discipline here and a wicket or two more can open the floodgates for them. An interesting hour of play coming up.
Extra bounce from a good length around off, Das stays back and defends it awkwardly to the off side. Finds the cover fielder again.
Gets behind the line of the delivery and defends it to covers.
FOUR! Excellent shot! Anderson Phillip hurls across a short delivery, around off, Litton Das rocks back and pulls it powerfully to the deep square leg fence.
On a good length, around off, Das is on the back foot as he blocks.
Goes short and around leg, Shakib pulls it to down to long leg for a run.
That is defended solidly off the front foot.
Short and wide outside off, Das cuts it with power to the off side but picks the cover-point fielder.
A bit of width there outside off, Litton doesn't go hard at it and just plays it down softly to point.
Angling it in, on a length, Das covers the line and blocks it safely.
On a length, around off, Das defends it well by taking the bottom hand off the handle.
Shortish and on off, Das stays back and quietly runs it down to third man for a couple of runs.

Aerial but just out of the grasp of the cover fielder. Jayden Seales delivers it on a length and outside off, Shakib plays a loose drive towards covers where the fielder leaps but it beats his outstretched left hand and races behind. They take three runs.
Jayden Seales (6-3-16-0) is back into the attack.
Around off, that is defended solidly off the front foot.
FOUR! Short in length and wide outside off, Litton Das latches onto it and slaps it through cover-point for a boundary.
A surprise short ball, around off, Das plays a reactive pull shot without much timing. Clears mid-wicket somehow and collects a brace.
A confident drive off the front foot by Das but he fails to beat the diving short extra cover fielder cleanly. That fielder parries the ball to mid off.
The batter has just watchfully blocked this out.
There seems to be some problem with the sightscreen! Litton Das walks to the umpire and signals something towards the sightscreen. All is good now and we are ready to resume.
Around off, on a length, shaping in, Das defends it down.

FOUR! Flashes and flashes hard! Short in length and outside off, Shakib walks forward and throws his bat at it. It flies off the outer half but goes through the vacant space at backward point for a boundary.
A bumper around leg, this time Shakib Al Hasan stays back and ducks.
Shakib looks to march forward and hence Kyle Mayers digs it in short. The Bangla skipper is forced to duck.
Outside off, played down to covers.
Shakib Al Hasan walks out to the middle now.

OUT! LBW! Kyle Mayers has trapped Shanto in front of the wickets with an inswinger. He delivers it on a length and around off, shaping in with some extra bounce at 121 kph. Najmul Hossain Shanto's front foot doesn't come far forward as he attempts to work it around the corner. He is thudded on the pads, they appeal and the finger has gone up again. DRS is taken by Shanto. UltraEdge finds no spike and Ball Tracking again shows that it's the UMPIRE'S CALL on hitting the wickets - it's clipping the top of leg. West Indies have been lucky with the last two wickets and Najmul Hossain Shanto trudges back.
Commentary.Howout: lbw b Kyle Mayers

Commentary.Commentary: Serves it on a length, outside off and shaping away, Shanto leaves it unattended.
Bowls it on a length and outside off, Das allows it through to the keeper.
On a length and around off, Das defends it solidly off the front foot.
Litton Das is the next man in.

OUT! Given lbw! A 132 kph delivery, an inswinger landing on a length around off and staying down a shade. Anamul Haque fails to defend it out and is pinged on the front pad. They appeal and the umpire lifts his finger. Haque has a word with his partner and takes the DRS. There is no need to look at the UltraEdge as the bat is quite far away. Ball Tracking rolls and finds that it's hitting the stumps and the impact is with the umpire's call. The onfield decision stays and Anderson Phillip has picked his second wicket, again with an inswinger. The only good thing for Bangladesh is that they retain the review.
Commentary.Howout: lbw b Anderson Phillip

Commentary.Commentary: Back of a length, outside off, Anamul stays back and plays it down to gully.
Uses his wrists to a length ball on middle and drops it in the gap at mid-wicket for a single.
Starts with a length ball around middle, Shanto defends it near his front pad and pushes it towards mid on.
Anderson Phillip (4-0-15-1) is brought back into the attack.
Lands it on a length and around off, Anamul Haque defends it from the back foot to the off side.

FOUR! It's uppish for a brief period but goes down the ground for a boundary. Anamul is not looking assured at the moment. Fuller and around off, Haque drives it back, it's aerial but wide of the bowler and mid off for a boundary.
That's too loose. Full and wide outside off, Anamul Haque has a lazy waft at it and misses.
On a length and outside off, tapped down to gully.

EDGY FOUR! A little bit of away movement from a length outside off, Anamul has a needless poke inside the line and edges it behind. It falls short of Campbell at first slip and races behind for a boundary. 100 comes up in a streaky manner.
Mayers bowls a shorter one, outside off, Anamul has nothing to do with it.
Fuller this time, outside off, no movement whatsoever, Shanto makes an easy leave to end the over.
Slightly short in length and outside off, Shanto stands back to protect his stumps and allows it through.
Serves it on a length and wide outside off, Shanto covers his stumps and shoulders arms.
FOUR! Well played! Roach digs it in short, around off, Shanto picks it very early, swivels on the back foot and pulls it with a lot of control through backward square leg.
Roach gets a bit close to the off stump, not close enough though as Shanto leaves this length delivery easily.
Pitches it up but quite wide outside off, an easy leave for Shanto.
Hurls it across on a length and outside off, going straight on with some extra bounce, Anamul covers the line and allows it through.
Back of a length, around middle, Shanto goes on the back foot and nurdles it down to fine leg for a run.
Fullish and close to off, cutting back in, Shanto defends it from the inner half of his blade to the leg side.
Fuller and on off, driven in control this time, but again towards the cover fielder.

Living dangerously. Shanto has played a couple of aerial shots on the off side now, post Lunch. On a length and outside off, Najmul Hossain Shanto is early into the drive but his aerial shot falls wide of the cover fielder.
Angles in a length ball on off, Shanto deals with the little extra bounce well as he jams it down on the surface.
Lands on a length, on off. Anamul Haque is happy to just block it out.
Roach goes short angling into middle from 'round the wicket. Shanto pulls it towards deep mid-wicket for a single.

Beaten! This is a lovely delivery that is pitched on a good length, outside off. Shanto looks to defend it off the front foot. However, the ball straightens after pitching and beats the outside edge of Shanto's blade.
Roach with a back-of-a-length delivery on off. Shanto blocks it off the back foot.
On a length, outside off. Shanto lets it go.
This is a fullish-length delivery outside off. Shanto drives it off the outside half of his blade towards point.
Serves a length delivery on off again. Anamul Haque with a good defensive technique again.
On a length, on off. Anamul Haque with a solid block this time.

Seales with a very good effort at point. Stops a certain boundary here! This is full and outside off. Anamul Haque drives it square of the wicket and it goes to the left of point. However, Seales dives and half-stops it. Two runs in the end.
Mayers pulls his length back, on off. Anamul Haque blocks it out.
FOUR! Third boundary for Anamul Haque and all of them have been pure class! This is a half-volley, outside off. Anamul Haque lunges forward and creams it through covers for a boundary.
Lands on a length, outside off. Anamul Haque leaves it alone.
This is good batting from Shanto, he is leaving the ball with great conviction in this Test match. On a length, outside off. Shanto lets it go.
Lands on a good length, outside off. Shanto with a watchful leave.
Gets it through the gap and two runs more added to the total. Back of a length, around off. Shanto cuts it right of point and comes back for the second run before the fielder cuts it off.
On a length, on off. Shanto with a solid forward defense.
Roach adjusts his length by pulling it back a bit, outside off. Shanto lets it go.
Roach also starts with a full delivery, outside off. Shanto drives but finds the fielder at covers.
Kemar Roach (6-1-17-0) to bowl from the other end.
Pulls his length back a bit, on off. Anamul Haque blocks it from his crease.
FOUR! Nicely played! Mayers with an overpitched delivery, around off. Anamul Haque leans forward and drives it beautifully through covers for a boundary.
This one shapes nicely into the batter. On a length, around off. Anamul Haque goes back and defends it behind square on the off side.
Full again but the line is outside off and Anamul Haque leaves it alone.
Full again and angling into middle. Shanto clips it to mid-wicket. The fielder there misfields and a single is taken.
Starts with a fuller delivery on off. Shanto drives left of the bowler. Mayers looks to stop it but the ball deflects off his hands onto the stumps at his end. Anamul Haque is safely in though.

We are back for the afternoon session! The West Indies players make their way out to the middle. Najmul Hossain Shanto and Anamul Haque, the two young Bangladesh batters, also walk out to resume their innings. This is going to be a very crucial session and it will be Kyle Mayers to start with the ball. Najmul Hossain Shanto is on strike. Here we go...
… DAY 1, SESSION 2 …

West Indies didn't extract the kind of movement and bounce that was expected this morning. To add to it, they bowled too many boundary deliveries, which allowed Bangladesh off the hook. Debutant Anderson Phillip provided them with the first breakthrough, and then a loose shot saw the downfall of Tamim minutes before Lunch. The tourists have fared a lot better with the bat, left the balls quite patiently, and the same kind of application will be expected from them in the afternoon session. Can they build on their start? Do join us at 10.10 pm IST (4.40 pm GMT) to find out.

The wicket of Tamim Iqbal at the backend, otherwise it was turning out to be that kind of a session which would have put a big smile on the face of Bangladesh. The conditions were expected to be tough, the history of this venue certainly suggested so, and losing the toss was the last thing the visiting team would have wished for! That said and done, Shakib's boys responded with a lot of guts and application. Tamim Iqbal led from the front with his positive attitude, and Mahmudul Hasan Joy also offered decent support in seeing off the new ball. The West Indian bowlers tried almost everything but without much success in the first hour.
Lands on a length and angling into off. Anamul Haque gets a good stride forward and defends it solidly. At Lunch on Day 1, Bangladesh are 77/2!

Takes a blow on his body! Jayden Seales pitches it short but it's not short enough to duck. Anamul Haque takes his eyes off the ball and tries to duck. It hits him on the back and rolls on the leg side. Poor technique.
A fullish delivery on off. Anamul Haque defends it back to the bowler.
On a length, on off. Anamul Haque blocks it out.

Well played in the end but a bit of indecision in that shot! A good-length delivery that comes in with the angle, around off. Anamul Haque first sets up to leave it but then puts his bat down just in time. The ball goes on the bounce to the third slip off the outside half.
Angles a length delivery on off. Anamul Haque blocks it off the front foot.
Lands on a length and it is a bit wider outside off. Shanto comfortably leaves it.
A fullish delivery, around off. Shanto makes a good leave.
A tad fuller and on off. Anamul Haque pushes it gently towards the off side and takes a single.
A good-length delivery, outside off. Anamul Haque lets it go.
Joseph pulls his length back and delivers it on the off-stump line. Anamul Haque defends it off the back foot.
FOUR! Anamul Haque gets off the mark with a lovely shot in his comeback game. This is full on middle, Anamul Haque drives it crisply past mid on for a boundary.
Back of a length, on off. Shanto is right behind it to block it.
FOUR! Confident pull shot from Shanto! Seales bangs it short on off. Shanto decides to take him on and pulls it towards the mid-wicket fence for a boundary.
Back of a length, on off. Shanto blocks it solidly off the back foot.
Seales bowls it closer to the off pole. Shanto drives it off the inside half of his blade towards the left of mid off.
Pulls his length back but it is again wide outside off. Shanto throws his bat at it but it is too wide and he does not connect.
Seales serves a full delivery, outside off. Shanto leaves it alone.
Jayden Seales will be eyeing another wicket before Lunch.
Angles a length delivery on middle. Haque clips it to short fine leg. End of a successful over from Alzarri Joseph!
On a length and outside off again. Anamul Haque lets it go again.
Lands on a good length, outside off. Anamul Haque leaves it alone.
Anamul Haque, the man making a comeback to the Test team after 8 years, walks in next. His last Test match was at this very venue where he managed scores of 9 and 0. Can he make a strong return?

OUT! CAUGHT! Ohh... Tamim Iqbal departs and looks a bit surprised but he has to go and this is a big, big breakthrough for West Indies. Alzarri Joseph keeps it on a fullish length at 136 kph. Not a half-volley exactly to drive it off the front foot. However, Tamim Iqbal decides to go for the shot. It is a loose attempt in the end and he gets the outside half of his blade. The ball loops up in the air towards point and Jermaine Blackwood there takes an easy catch.
Commentary.Howout: c Jermaine Blackwood b Alzarri Joseph

Commentary.Commentary: Goes fuller and straighter this time at 138 kph. Iqbal clips it through mid-wicket for a couple.
Back of a length, around off at 141 kph. Iqbal leaves it alone.
Maiden over! Raymon Reifer serves a length delivery, outside off. Shanto is happy to let it go.
This is full on off. Shanto drives but finds the mid on fielder again.
Lands on a length, around off. Shanto defends it with soft hands to the right of the point fielder.
Some issues with the shape of the ball. The umpire checks it through the ring and has asked for a replacement. A decent nut is being picked and here we go again...
Goes a tad fuller on middle at 130 kph. Shanto works it to the right of square leg.
Lands on a length, on off. Shanto defends it off the inside half of his blade to mid on.
Serves a full ball on off. Shanto drives but straight to mid on.
Goes short on middle. Good pace on this one as Iqbal is hurried into his pull shot and mistimes it to mid-wicket.
Hits the length hard and it is outside off. Tamim Iqbal leaves it alone.
Ohh...in that channel around off again! Lands on a good length and takes the ball away from the batter. Tamim Iqbal looks to defend but the ball beats the outside edge of his blade.
Back of a length, on middle. Tamim Iqbal defends it calmly towards the leg side.
A good-length delivery, outside off. Tamim Iqbal leaves it alone.

Good delivery to start a new spell by Alzarri Joseph! Keeps it a tad short and angles it across the batter. Iqbal gets a stride forward and then keeps his bat inside the line of the ball to let it go.
Back of a length, around off and shaping in a shade, Shanto mistimes his back-foot punch to covers. Once again the third umpire checks the front foot of the bowler, it's all good.
An attempted yorker on middle, at 128 kph, Najmul Hossain Shanto digs it out back to the bowler.
On a length and around off, Najmul Hossain Shanto defends it from the back foot.
Width there outside off, Tamim forces it from the back foot and sends it in the gap at cover-point. They cross for a run.
Lands it on a length and close to off, Tamim covers the line and defends it back.
FOUR! Superb timing! Raymon Reifer serves it full and around middle, Tamim Iqbal strides forward and receives the ball on top of the bounce as he clips it through mid-wicket.
Full and around middle, at 135 kph, it's defended off the front foot to mid off. A loud shout of 'no' echoes around the stadium.
FOUR! Fine, fine shot! This one is an over-pitched delivery, around middle at 135 kph, Najmul Hossain Shanto brings down a straight bat and caresses it down through mid on for a boundary.
Anderson Phillip cooks a 137 kph bouncer, around middle and Najmul Hossain Shanto ducks.
Fullish and on off, Shanto defends it right under his watchful eyes.
Back of a length, around middle and off, Shanto goes on the back foot to defend but it takes the inner half and rolls behind square leg. There is a fielder present.
Pitches it up and around off, Shanto leans forward and defends it firmly to mid off.
Fullish and on off, Tamim Iqbal gets forward and drives it back in the direction of the bowler. The third umpire checks the front foot but finds that it's a fair delivery.
Short in length and outside off, Shanto goes on the back foot and hits it through covers for a run.
Raymon pulls his length ball and serves outside off, Najmul Hossain Shanto walks down the track and then decides late to leave it.
Fuller and on off, Najmul Hossain Shanto presses forward and dead-bats it beside the pitch on the off side.
Serves it on a length and around off, Shanto defends it close to his body.
A tempter to begin the spell. Raymon Reifer serves it on a driving length outside off, Najmul Hossain Shanto leaves it alone.
Raymon Reifer is brought into the attack now.
Bends his back to bowl short and around off at 138 kph, Tamim leans back and allows it through.
Fuller and on middle, helped behind square leg for a single.
FOUR! A bouncer down the leg side, at 133 kph, Najmul goes on his toes to pull but perhaps only manages to glove it down to fine leg for a boundary.
Better from Shanto this time. A touch short in length, close to off and angling away at 137 kph, Najmul Hossain Shanto covers the line and shoulders arms.
Beaten by the angle. Anderson Phillip delivers it wide outside off, at 137 kph, Shanto pushes inside the line, away from his body, and is beaten.
Fractionally short and close to off, angling away at 134 kph, Tamim punches it to the left of point for a run.
Short in length and outside off at 138 kph, Najmul Hossain Shanto shapes up for the pull shot but mistimes it badly towards mid on.
Angles in a length ball, on middle and leg, Najmul Hossain Shanto works it across the line but finds backward short leg.
Shortish and on off, defended off the back foot.
That's a jaffa! Joseph hurries up the batter with a 140 kph bouncer. Around leg and Tamim leaps to fend it away. It perhaps goes off his gloves towards backward square leg and they cross. 50 up!
Back of a length, on top of off, Tamim defends it from the back foot.
FOUR! This is the eighth boundary from the bat of Tamim Iqbal this morning. Alzarri Joseph lands it on a good length and outside off, Tamim leans forward and crunches his drive through covers.
A bumper but down the leg side, Shanto is not bothered and lets it through to the keeper.
At 133 kph, Anderson Phillip delivers this around middle and off, on a length, Shanto blocks it from the back foot.
Pitches it a shade up this time, around leg, at 135 kph, Shanto leans forward and defends it from the inner half of his bat.
On a good length, around middle and off at 134 kph, Najmul Hossain Shanto is on the back foot as he defends it down.
Fuller in length and on the pads at 139 kph, Tamim flicks it across the line, a bit aerially but through the gap at square leg. A single is taken.
Serves it on a good length outside off, at 136 kph, shaping away, Tamim watches it and lets it go.
Bouncer around off, Najmul picks it early and ducks safely.
A bit too wide outside off, an easy leave for Najmul Hossain Shanto.
Alzarri Joseph follows up the last delivery with a full ball on the pads, Tamim leans across and flicks it to deep square leg for a run.

That's a snorter. Alzarri Joseph delivers it a bit short around middle, and gets a steep bounce, Tamim Iqbal tries to get away from the line of the fire but fails in doing so. He takes a blow on his right shoulder.
Full and around off, Tamim defends it back solidly.
Lands it on a good length around off, Tamim Iqbal defends it from the back foot.
A bit short and around leg, Shanto stands back and plays it down off his hips to square leg.
On a length but it's delivered on the pads, Shanto tickles it to deep square leg and opens his account with a couple of runs.
In the zone outside off, Shanto shoulders arms.
Delivers it on a length and around middle, Najmul Hossain Shanto tries to work it on the leg side but gets a soft leading edge to cover-point.

DRINKS! After a good solid start by Bangladesh, Anderson Phillip, the debutant has provided the breakthrough in his first over and brought some respite for the Windies. They would be looking to capitalise on this breakthrough now and get a couple of more wickets before Lunch. From Bangladesh's point of view, it is critical that they don't lose wickets in a cluster here and the new batter, Najmul Hossain Shanto needs to support Tamim Iqbal here who is batting quite well.

OUT! BOWLED! Anderson Phillip takes just two balls in Test cricket to pick his maiden wicket. What a moment for the young man and he is getting mobbed by his teammates. A lovely inswinger from him, on a length and around off, Mahmudul Hasan Joy shows very little footwork as he tries to defend it with a straight bat. It though nips back in to beat the bat and goes on to rattle the stumps. West Indies have their first breakthrough in the 13th over, can they capitalize now?
Commentary.Howout: b Anderson Phillip

Commentary.Commentary: Short and outside off, guided through point for two runs.
The debutant, Anderson Phillip is into the attack now.
Fuller and around off, driven to mid on.
Around middle and leg, defended on the leg side.
Beaten all ends up. Movement into the batter, Tamim is cut in half as he attempts to defend from the back foot.

SHOUT FOR A CAUGHT BEHIND! Nothing from the bowler, nothing from the umpire. 'I heard something', says Joshua Da Silva. He gets support from the slip cordon as well. Kraigg Brathwaite takes the DRS, believing them. Coming to the delivery - Alzarri Joseph switches to 'round the wicket and lands it close to off. It lands and straightens as Tamim tries to defend. It goes past the bat, there is some noise and West Indies opt for the referral. A big gap between bat and pad, shows the replay. No need to check the UltraEdge. Review wasted.
FOUR! No withdrawing of the bat this time. Short and wide outside off, begging to be hit, Tamim Iqbal rocks back and smacks it through point.
Beaten! Back of a length, close to off and leaving the batter with the angle, Tamim initially looks to play at it but then withdraws his bat.
Roach goes full, trying to target the pads, but it's easily worked away towards mid-wicket.
Lands it on a length and close to off, Mahmudul Hasan Joy gets behind the line and blocks it off his front foot.
Width outside off, short in length, Joy goes back to cut but finds the point fielder. Easy going for the Bangla openers thus far.
Fuller again, around off, this time Mahmudul Hasan Joy inside-edges his drive to mid on.
Pitches it up and outside off, Joy drives confidently off the front foot but finds mid off.
FOUR! Slapped! Short in length and outside off, Mahmudul Hasan Joy goes on his toes and cuts it firmly through point for a boundary.
So the Bangladesh openers have done well here to negotiate the first 10 overs without losing a wicket. On a length, drifting into the pads. Joy works it to fine leg for a single.
Keeps the length a tad short again, on middle. Iqbal works it towards mid-wicket for a single.
Back of a length again from Alzarri Joseph. On off and Iqbal rides the bounce to block it.
Shortish length, outside off. Iqbal cuts it to point this time.
FOUR! Tamim Iqbal has been positive today and has taken full advantage of anything loose! It is short and wide outside off. Iqbal cuts it uppishly towards the backward point region for a boundary.

Alzarri Joseph starts with a back-of-a-length delivery, outside off. Iqbal tries to punch it away but gets a thick inside edge and Joshua Da Silva behind the stumps makes a good stop diving to his right.
Alzarri Joseph comes into the attack.
Roach with a good-length delivery, outside off. Joy lets it go.
A fullish delivery on off. Joy drives it to mid off.

Finds the edge but it does not carry! Lands on a length, around off. Joy tries to defend it off the front foot. However, the ball catches the thick outside edge of his blade and goes on the bounce to the third slip fielder.
A full delivery on middle. Joy connects with his flick shot this time. It goes past square leg and the batters run two.
Roach goes fuller in search of that swing and ends up drifting it down the leg side. Joy tries to flick it but misses.
On a length, angling into off. Joy with a solid front-foot defense.
Seales looking to bowl it straighter but ends up drifting it way down the leg side. Iqbal looks to flick it but misses.
Another length delivery but this time it is angled into off. Iqbal looks to defend it off the front foot but gets an inside edge onto his pads.
Lands on a length, outside off. Tamim Iqbal lets it go.
FOUR! Wow! Tamim Iqbal is looking in great touch here! This is full and outside off. Tamim Iqbal lunges forward and drives it crisply through covers for another good-looking boundary.
Pulls his length back and the line is wider too. Iqbal leaves it.
FOUR! Top-class from Tamim Iqbal! Seales bowls an overpitched delivery on off. Iqbal leans forward and drives it past mid off for a lovely boundary.
On a fuller length, around off. Joy looks to drive but bottom-edges it on the surface. Eventful over from Roach.

HUGE SHOUT AGAIN! The finger goes up again. Another review. This time Kemar Roach spears in a near-yorker, around middle and leg, Mahmudul Hasan Joy leans across to flick but misses. He is rapped on the pads, they appeal and the umpire agrees. Joy takes the DRS. It's MISSING THE STUMPS! Smiles all around. Twice Mahmudul Hasan Joy has been saved by the technology.

Appeal for an lbw, given out. Good review by Mahmudul Hasan Joy! Roach delivers it on a fullish length and it is that inswinger angling into the batter. Joy looks to defend but misses. The ball hits his pads and there is an appeal. The umpire raises his finger but Joy after consulting his partner takes a review. The UltraEdge shows no bat involved and the Ball Tracking shows that it is missing the leg stump. So West Indies have to wait for that first breakthrough!
Outside off, left alone.
The batter goes back in his crease to flick but cannot find the gap.
Sliding down the leg side, Joy tries to flick but misses. It goes off his pads to short leg.
A short ball on middle to end the over! Tamim Iqbal ducks under it.
On a length and outside off. Iqbal drives it off the front foot and the ball goes off the bounce to the point fielder.

FOUR! Good controlled shot from Tamim Iqbal! Seales lands it on a length and around off. Iqbal presses forward with soft hands and opens the face of this blade a little bit. The ball runs through the gully region for a boundary.
Seales continues with that fullish length outside off and Tamim Iqbal is happy to let the ball pass.
Seales delivers it fuller again and wider outside off. Iqbal leaves it alone.
Seales goes fuller and outside off. Tamim Iqbal lets it go.
A fullish delivery, on off. Iqbal pushes it gently towards covers and takes a single.
Angles it on leg. Maybe looking for that inswinging delivery. On a length and Iqbal looks to clip it but misses. The ball hits his thigh pad and goes towards the leg side.
Pulls his length back and it is around off again. Iqbal adjusts to the length of the ball and defends it towards point.
Roach with an overpitched delivery, around off. Tamim Iqbal with a stylish drive but finds the fielder at covers.
Joy is off the mark, finally! Back of a length and outside off. Joy rides the bounce and punches it through covers for a single.
Back of a length, on off. Joy goes back in his crease and blocks it solidly.
Lands on a good length and just around off. Tamim Iqbal with a good leave again.
Goes outside off and a bit fuller this time. However, Tamim Iqbal is not keen to play this one.
Back of a length, on middle. Tamim works it towards the leg side.
Good delivery! After a wide full ball, Seales follows it up with a bouncer on middle. Iqbal ducks under it.
This is the shot, he needs to be more careful of! Seales goes fuller and wider outside off. Iqbal goes for a big booming drive away from his body and gets beaten on the outside edge.
Seales serves a good-length delivery, outside off. Iqbal makes a good leave. Not much swing out there so far for the Windies bowlers.
Roach delivers this on a length and close to off. However, Joy is solid in defense.
Roach bowls a good-length delivery, outside off and Joy is just happy to let it go.
Good positive running! Back of a length, around off. Iqbal punches it with soft hands towards cover-point and takes a single.
Angling into middle, on a length. Iqbal defends it towards mid-wicket.

Bit of indecision from Tamim Iqbal! On a length and around off. It is seaming away a bit and Iqbal decides to leave it at the last moment. The ball catches the inside edge of his blade and luckily goes just past the stumps.
FOUR! Beautifully played! Roach bowls a half-volley on off. Iqbal gets a good stride forward and creams this drive through covers for a boundary.
Another delivery that is pitched on a length and going down leg. Joy decides to let it go.
On a good length and outside off. Joy with a watchful leave this time.
This is full and drifting down the leg side. Joy looks to flick it away but misses.
Another delivery on a good length, on off. Joy blocks it out.
Lands on a length and around off. A hint of away movement there. Joy presses forward to defend and gets a thick outside edge towards the third slip fielder. Luckily it does not carry.
On a length, on off. Joy blocks it from his crease.
Jayden Seales to share the new ball from the opposite end.

FOUR! Good shot and Tamim Iqbal and Bangladesh are underway with a boundary! This is full and again that inswinging delivery drifting into the pads. Iqbal this time clips it through square leg for a boundary.

Huge shout for an lbw! The finger stays down. Kraigg Brathwaite has an extended chat with his bowler and then takes the DRS at the last moment. There doesn't appear to be any bat involved, the UltraEdge confirms the same. Ball Tracking shows that it's clipping the leg stump. Umpire's call. Coming to the ball - This one is much fuller by Roach and it swings into the batter on middle and leg. Iqbal looks to flick it away but misses. He is rapped up on the pads and luckily for him, it is the umpire's call on hitting the wickets.
Lands on a length, around off. Iqbal with a solid block off the front foot.

Oh...that takes off from a length! Is this the sign of things to come? Welcome to St Lucia! Roach pulls his length back slightly here and delivers it around off. Iqbal looks to defend it off the front foot but the ball bounces sharply and hits his gloves. Luckily for Tamim Iqbal, it just rolls towards the gully region.
Roach now delivers it closer to the off pole, on a length again and Iqbal blocks it off the front foot.
Roach comes 'round the wicket and lands i on a good length, outside off. Iqbal keeps his bat inside the line of the ball and lets it go.

Right then, it's time to get underway. Anderson Phillip gets his Test cap from Kemar Roach, and now the West Indian players are spreading on the field. ​Tamim Iqbal and Mahmudul Hasan Joy are the openers for Bangladesh. It's going to be their nemesis, Kemar Roach, to kick start proceedings with the new ball. Both teams take the knee to show their support for the BLM movement. Let's play...

Pitch Report - Stacy-Ann King is inspecting the playing area. She says that the sun is out and there is a nice calming breeze blowing across the ground. Adds that the pitch looks good and there is some grass and it will assist the pacers. Tells that it is hard in nature and this pitch generally helps the fast bowlers. Mentions that batting in the first innings will be crucial and there might be some help for the spinners later in the game.

Shakib Al Hasan, the Bangla skipper, says that he would have loved to bowl first but adds that it seems to be a better wicket than Antigua where the bounce will be true. Adds that he wants his batters to be mentally tough and if they overcome the tough period initially, they are capable of scoring big. Informs that Mustafizur Rahman and Mominul Haque make way for  Shoriful Islam and Anamul Haque.

Kraigg Brathwaite, the captain of West Indies, says that they are bowling as here at St Lucia there is something for the bowlers early on. Adds that he is not taking any Test match lightly and wants his team to keep improving and stay disciplined. Informs that Anderson Phillip is making his Test debut and he comes in place of Gudakesh Motie.
Did you know? Anamul Haque last played a Test match for Bangladesh in 2014 and that was at this very venue in Gros Islet. Life comes a full circle for him.

Bangladesh (Playing XI) - Tamim Iqbal, Mahmudul Hasan Joy, Najmul Hossain Shanto, Anamul Haque (In place of Mominul Haque), Litton Das, Shakib Al Hasan (C), Nurul Hasan (WK), Mehidy Hasan, Ebadot Hossain, Khaled Ahmed, Shoriful Islam (In place of Mustafizur Rahman).

West Indies (Playing XI) - Kraigg Brathwaite (C), John Campbell, Raymon Reifer, Nkrumah Bonner, Jermaine Blackwood, Kyle Mayers, Joshua Da Silva (WK), Alzarri Joseph, Kemar Roach, Jayden Seales, Anderson Phillip (On debut) (In place of Gudakesh Motie).
TOSS - The coin goes up and lands in favour of Kraigg Brathwaite. The West Indies have elected to BOWL first.

As we build towards this game, there is some engrossing cricket going around in the world. At Headingley, England have lost two early wickets after bundling out New Zealand for 329 this morning while in the Island country of Sri Lanka, the hosts have made some serious inroads with three early wickets after getting bowled out for a below-par total of 160 with the bat. We will keep you updated with all the action from these games and as far as this game is concerned, we are just moments away from a very crucial toss. Stay tuned.

We are back! Bangladesh have an uphill task of wiping off the Windies' lead of 174 runs and then setting a target. The umpires and the players are back on the field. Tamim Iqbal and Mahmudul Hasan Joy are all set to open the innings for Bangladesh. As usual, Kemar Roach has the new ball in hand and is raring to go. Let's play...
...Third Innings...

West Indies were off to a superb start with Kraigg Brathwaite and John Campbell putting a century opening stand but after that, the Windies started to lose the grip and were looking in a bit of trouble. Kyle Mayers and Jermaine Blackwood joined to repair things and the duo added around 100-odd runs to put their team in lead. Once, Blackwood fell, Mayers started to show his muscle as he scored at a quick rate. He and Joshua Da Silva helped West Indies get past the 100 lead but Day 3 wasn't what they hoped for as only 68 runs came through. Excellent bowling performance from Khaled Ahmed, he ended with five wickets while Hasan got three and he was the initiater and these two made sure Bangladesh do not give away a big lead.

So, West Indies have a lead of 174 runs. It was Kyle Mayers who was there in the middle and was building on the overnight lead but once his wicket fell there wasn't much batting from the other side. Credit to Bangladesh bowlers, they have not allowed much runs to score and took all the wickets quickly. Joshua Da Silva went early and then, they kept things tight further to bundle out West Indies for 408.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! Jubilation for Khaled Ahmed as he gets his maiden five-wicket haul in Test cricket. Lovely delivery this, around the top of off and just shaping away a touch after pitching. Jayden Seales has a little dab at it and gets the outside edge. Nurul Hasan dives down to his left to take a good catch. West Indies bowled out for 408 and they lead by 174 runs!
Commentary.Howout: c Nurul Hasan b Khaled Ahmed

Commentary.Commentary: Around the top of off, kept out on the off side by Seales.
FOUR! Nicely done in the end by Jayden Seales. This is very full and on off, Seales squeezes it out with soft hands and the ball runs away through the vacant backward point region for a boundary.
Full and on the pads, flicked away to fine leg for a single. The lead now grows to 170.
Jayden Seales is the last man in.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! Brilliant comeback delivery from Shoriful Islam, goes a bit fuller and angles it in closer to the off pole. Anderson Phillip opts to drive at it with a straight bat but seems to have got beaten past the outside edge. Appeal for a caught behind...not given! The keeper seems interested and Shakib Al Hasan does go upstairs. The replay shows that it is close to the bat and UltraEdge confirms there is a faint edge. OUT!
Commentary.Howout: c Nurul Hasan b Shoriful Islam

Commentary.Commentary: EDGED AND FOUR! Good length, outside off. Anderson Phillip takes a step forward and throws his bat at it. The ball goes off the top edge and flies over the slip cordon running away into the fence. 400 is up now for West Indies.
Switches to around the wicket now and angles it on the body, Phillip nudges it out on the leg side.
A length ball, on middle, kept out by Phillip.
Around the top of off, angling across the batter. Anderson Phillip is a bit late but manages to defend it out.
Length again, this time on a tighter line, Roach makes the leave.
FOUR! Cracking shot! Length ball, outside off. Kemar Roach stands tall and drives through the line of the ball, dispatching it into the cover fence.
Full and straight, pushed back towards the bowler.
Short of a good length, at the stumps. Roach defends it out.
Leg bye! This is short and at the body, Anderson Phillip tries to fend it off awkwardly. The ball goes off his hips and towards backward square leg. They get a leg bye.
Pitches it up, around off but it is the slower delivery. Phillip blocks it off the front foot.
Short again, this time around off. Roach sways away from the line of the ball.
A touch fuller and slanted across the right-hander. Kemar Roach watches it go past him and into the mitts of the keeper.
Good short ball, banged in around leg stump. Roach ducks under it well.
Length again, on off, Roach plays it towards mid off.
Much better from Islam. Top of off line, Roach blocks it out.
FOUR! Valuable runs here for West Indies and they will take it. Half-volley, wide of off and Kemar Roach creams it through cover-point for a boundary.
Shoriful Islam comes back into the attack, replacing Mehidy Hasan.
FOUR! Glorious shot from Anderson Phillip and that's his first boundary in Test cricket. Overpitched, around off, Phillip drives it past the man at mid off and the ball goes into the fence.

Length again, around off, Phillip keeps it out on the leg side.

A tad shorter and on leg stump, Roach goes deep in his crease to nudge it leg side.
Quicker through the air, around leg. Kemar Roach makes a solid defensive block.
On leg stump, Roach defends it out.
Beaten! This is just drifted across the right-hander from around the wicket. Roach looks to defend but gets beaten past the outside edge.

Full and on leg stump, Roach clips it leg side but can't get it past mid-wicket. Maiden!

On a good length and over off, Roach hops on the back foot to keep it out.

Turning into the pads, Roach knocks it 'round the corner for a single.

On off, Roach strides forward to defend.
On a length, turning in from the off pole. Kemar Roach stays solid in defense.

Mehidy Hasan to continue from the opposite end.

Quicker, fuller and on off. Roach rocks back and makes another solid block.
Another solid block from Roach.
Tossed up on middle. Blocked out.

Flatter, outside off, turning more away. Mayers lets it go.

Too full and on off. Defended out.
Outside off again, this one stays low. Roach shoulders arms to it.
Outside off. Left alone.
Short in length and outside off. It climbs on Roach who dabs it past backward point for a couple of runs. Slow surface there.

Mayers is up and running on Day 3! Length and on off. He taps it to covers for a quick single.

We are ready for action on Day 3! There are some clouds hovering around the ground but for the moment, the sun is peeping through those clouds. The umpires and the players are out in the middle with Kyle Mayers and Joshua Da Silva set to resume their stay at the crease. Khaled Ahmed to start proceedings with the ball on Day 3. Let's play...

PITCH REPORT - Stacy-Ann King and Samuel Badree are pitchside. Badree says that there has been some overnight and early morning rain but hopes the day remains free of rain. Adds that the pitch is a bit grassy. King adds that Day 2 was good for batting but there's some moisture today and the Bangladeshi bowlers might get more out of the pitch early on Day 3.

Jermaine Blackwood is down for a quick chat. He says that batting wise it was great and Kyle Mayers scoring his second Test ton was commendable and is happy for him. Mentions that he loves batting with Mayers and they gel well together and both of them can score at will but he was trying to support Mayers yesterday. Adds that now he takes a lot more overs to get in and has made a slight change in the way he bats and it is coming off for him.

Bangladesh bowlers toiled hard on Day 2 but they allowed two big partnerships to happen and that took the game a bit away from them. The visitors will try and make an impact in the first hour itself or else Kyle Mayers will flex his muscles once again and Bangladesh will fall more behind in this game. Who do you think will dominate the opening session? We wait to find out. Stay tuned for further updates.

Hello everyone! Welcome to the action of Day 3 in this second Test match between Bangladesh and West Indies. The hosts are pretty well ahead in this game as they lead by 106 runs with 5 wickets in hand. They have two set-batters at the crease who look pretty much in a comfortable position after a bit of panic situation created due to losing a flurry of wickets. The openers got off to a good start and later, as West Indies were slipping away, Kyle Mayers and Jermaine Blackwood put on a stand of more than 100. Blackwood fell but Joshua Da Silva made sure that they end Day 2 on a high.
...Day 3, Session 1...

That's a wrap to the second day's play. West Indies have wrestled back the control of this Test match and can dictate terms. Bangladesh, on the flip side, once again find themselves behind the 8-ball and will need a big effort on Sunday to stay relevant. The first ball on Day 3 will be bowled at 7.30 pm IST (2 pm GMT), but as usual, our build-up will begin well in advance. Don't forget to join us. Cheers!

The evening session started with an early wicket for the tourists as they got rid of Blackwood. Bangladesh served 12 overs of spin bowling after Tea, in the span of 30 minutes or so, as they tried to rush through their overs. Bangladesh could have attacked the new batter more with their pacers but they decided otherwise which in a way allowed Joshua Da Silva to settle down. After delaying the second new ball by four overs, once the tourists took it, both the batters started to deal with it easily and the runs also came at a good click.

John Campbell comes up for a chat! The West Indian opener says that he was pretty pleased to get a century stand with Kraigg Brathwaite. Tells that a lot of balls kept a bit low on Day 1 and the bounce was pretty uneven. Tells that Kyle Mayers' knock was very special and he feels that it has set up the game perfectly for them. Mentions that a lead over 100 is pretty handy on this surface.

There was a period on Day 2 when the hosts were under the cosh. Bangladesh had the momentum behind them and looked threatening to run through the West Indian batting order. But two individuals known for their aggressive batting style, Kyle Mayers and Jermaine Blackwood, joined forces and adopted a phlegmatic approach. Kyle was still the aggressor in their century stand, ready to flex his muscles whenever the opportunity presented itself, while Blackwood remained calm and composed. It was prudent cricket from the pair where they showed plenty of resolve and fortitude.

A terrific day of Test cricket comes to a close. Bangladesh needed a strong performance after a below-par outing on Day 1, but they struggled to make early inroads. However, 30 minutes before the Lunch break, they struck gold and picked up wickets in a cluster to peg the home team on the back foot. Just when this Test match started to tilt in their favour, the afternoon session happened, a wicket-less one, and that took the wind out of the Bangladesh sails.

Satisfaction and relief writ large on the faces of the West Indian players. Kyle Mayers returns after doing a responsible job for his team. An unbeaten century against his name! The feeling must be great as he raises his bat on his way to the dressing room. His 92-run stand with Joshua Da Silva has cornered the Bangla team and West Indies have built a lead of 106 runs with five wickets left in the kitty.

Tossed up on off. Mayers blocks it off the front foot.
Lands on a length, outside off. Joshua Da Silva steers it through the gully region for a couple.

The most impressive thing about this knock is that he came in when his team was under some serious pressure, he weathered the storm and is now cashing in!
