Fuller and on middle, Mayer lunges and defends it to mid on.
Angles it in, on a good length around middle, staying low, Joshua Da Silva does well to keep it out towards square leg.
Shortish and outside off, Joshua remains on the back foot and pushes it to covers.
On middle, a length ball, Mayers drops it with gentle hands to covers and pinches a single. Moves to 89!
FOUR! Sumptuous looking shot! Back of a length, around off, Kyle Mayers camps back and sweetly punches it through covers for a boundary.
A touch short and on middle, Mayers sticks on the back foot and blocks it towards mid off.
On a length, around off, Kyle defends it from the back foot to covers.
Flighted and full, around off, Joshua Da Silva continues to defend from the back foot.
Drags his length short, around off, Joshua pulls but finds the mid-wicket fielder.
Tossed up, around off, Da Silva defends it from the back foot.
Spinning down the leg side, the batter offers no shot and pads it away.
Fuller again, around middle, pushed down to mid on.
Floated delivery, landing full and around off, Joshua Da Silva lunges and defends.
Fullish and around off, Mayers pushes it firmly to covers.

EDGY FOUR! Mayers is taking a lot of risk at the moment and it's paying off as well. This one is on a length and outside off, Mayers goes for a drive through the line but it takes the outside edge and flies wide of second slip. He moves to 84!
Identical to the last delivery, this time Mayers uses his bat and defends it on the leg side.
Around leg, landing on a length and skidding off the surface, Mayers is caught on the back foot, attempting to flick but misses. There is a shout for an lbw, not given. Perhaps, pitching outside leg.
Khaled goes length and delivers it on middle and leg, Kyle defends it by getting half-forward.
FOUR! Streaky! Short in length, outside off, extra pace and bounce there for Khaled, Mayers throws his bat at it and the outside edge flies over the slip cordon for a boundary.
Khaled Ahmed replaces Shoriful Islam now.
Flighted around off, full and going straight on, rather than coming forward, Joshua Da Silva defends it from the back foot.
Short and on off, punched to deep point for a single.
Slightly short and outside off, Mayers plays a controlled square cut to point.
Floated one, full and around leg, it's defended down on the surface.
Fullish and around leg, flicked across the line but straight to short leg.
FOUR! Shot! Full and flighted outside off, Mayers takes a good stride forward and bludgeons his drive through covers for a boundary.
In the channel outside off, left alone.
That is defended solidly off the front foot.
Outside off, no shot offered.
On a good length around middle, staying down, Da Silva defends it to mid-wicket.
Fuller and outside off, Joshua Da Silva mistimes his drive to mid off.
Outside off, tapped down to point for a run.
Flatter again, on off, defended from the back foot.
Quicker through the air, full and on off, Joshua Da Silva defends it from the back foot.
Stays on the back foot to a short ball and works it in front of square leg.
Loopy this time, full and around off, Joshua Da Silva presses forward and defends it to the off side.
Very full again, as it's fired on middle, Joshua Da Silva pushes it down to mid on.
Too full in length and on middle, Mayers hits it firmly down to long on for a run.
On a length and outside off, angling away, Joshua Da Silva shoulders arms.
Around off, on a length, Joshua stays watchful on the back foot and defends it to the off side.
Width there outside off, short in length, Mayers rocks back and slams it over covers. The point fielder cuts it off running across to his left and they get three runs.
Shoriful bowls it on a good length outside off, Kyle gets forward to push inside the line and runs it down off the outer edge to third man. They take two.
Lands it on a good length, outside off and going straight on, Mayers covers his stumps and shoulders arms.
Drags it on, nearly. Full in length and outside off, Mayers tries to drive but it takes the inner edge and rolls on the leg side.
The second new ball has been taken by Bangladesh! Shakib Al Hasan delayed it by four overs and let's see how things pan out with this brand new ball. Also, Shoriful Islam is back into the attack.
Loopy delivery, full and outside off, Joshua Da Silva lunges and defends it to safety. So in the last 32 minutes or so, Bangladesh have fired in 12 overs.
Flatter through the air, outside off and short once more, Joshua Da Silva is at ease in defending it down.
Short again, around off, Joshua Da Silva hangs back and punches it to mid-wicket.
A touch short and on off, this time the batter defends it from the back foot.
Full and flighted on off, defended back off the front foot.
Spinning down the leg side, Joshua Da Silva flicks but it hits the short leg fielder.
Flatter ball, around off, blocked safely from the back foot.
Skidding down the leg side, Joshua gets some bat behind it and sends it down to fine leg. The fielder chases it down and they take three runs.
Very full this time, around middle, it's been pushed down to long on for a run.
Quicker and on middle, Mayers moves back and wrists it to mid-wicket again.
Fuller again, around leg, Mayers flicks but finds short mid-wicket.
Flatter and fuller, around off, Mayers is on the front foot as he defends.
The reserve umpire comes out and hands the new ball to one of the umpires. Bangladesh have not opted for it yet.
Beats the bat! Drifting in close to off, Joshua Da Silva tries to defend the line but it straightens to beat the outside edge.
Extra airtime to this delivery, around off, Joshua Da Silva prefers to block it from the back foot.
Quicker off spinner on middle, Joshua Da Silva defends it from the back foot.
Too full again, but around leg, Mayers knocks it down to long on for a single.
Fuller and on off, driven firmly off the front foot to covers.
Flighted and on off, Kyle defends it by getting forward.
Will Shakib Al Hasan take the new ball here? No, it will be Mehidy Hasan to continue.
Nicely floated, full and on off, Joshua Da Silva presses forward and defends. They are rushing through their overs.
Fuller and outside off, Da Silva drives it to cover-point.
Slower through the air, short and outside off, Joshua Da Silva punches it to covers.
Leans forward to a full ball and blocks it to the off side.
Short and around off, Joshua gets back and works it to square leg.
Flatter and fuller on middle, defended back.
Bangladesh bowled the last 8 overs in no time and the second new ball is available now! They have decided to not take it immediately though.
Risky leave, this! Mehidy Hasan pitches it on off and the ball turns away a bit. Kyle Mayers leaves it trusting on the turn Mehidy will get.
Shout for a catch, the umpire shakes his head. No review is taken. Flighted and around leg, Mayers tries to defend but misses. It goes off his pads to first slip.
Slower through the air, on off. Mayers pushes it towards covers.
This is on off. Mayers defends it again off the front foot.
Almost the same line and Mayers gets to the pitch of the ball to defend it.
Pitches it around leg. Mayers defends it off the front foot.
Tossed-up delivery on off. Joshua Da Silva gets a good stride forward and blocks it out.
Pushes it quicker and angles it on middle again. Joshua Da Silva nudges it towards the leg side.
On middle and fuller again. Joshua Da Silva works it to short mid-wicket.
Drifting on the pads. Joshua Da Silva clips it past square leg for a couple.
On middle and slower through the air. Joshua Da Silva works it towards mid-wicket.
Ohh...that was close! An arm ball, around off. It comes in with the angle and Joshua Da Silva leaves it. That was inches away from the off pole.
Pushes it quicker but the same line again. Mayers is solid in his front-foot defense.
Slower through the air, on off. Mayers blocks it out.
A fuller one on off. Mayers drives it to covers.
Good running! This is tossed up on off again. Joshua Da Silva pushes it to mid on and sets off for a single. The fielder there fails to collect it cleanly and a single is completed.
Tossed up again on off. Joshua Da Silva pushes it to mid on.

That single brings up 250 for the West Indies! Another misfield this time from the bowler. Tossed up on off. Mayers drives it back to the bowler. Hasan fails to collect it cleanly and a single is taken.
Tossed up on off. Mayers tries to hit it away down the ground. The ball goes towards mid off. Shoriful Islam misfields and a single is taken.
Loopy and full, around off, Mayers drives but finds mid off this time.
Too full and around off, Mayers mistimes his drive to covers.
Sliding down around leg, Mayers goes back and flicks it to square leg.
Leans forward to a full ball and jams it down safely.
Fires it full and around off, Mayers flicks it to mid-wicket.
Goes shorter on off. Joshua Da Silva is right behind it to block it.
Tossed up on off. Defended off the front foot.
This is slightly shorter on off. Joshua Da Silva defends it towards the off side.
Fuller on middle. Joshua Da Silva blocks it out.
Slower through the air on off. Joshua Da Silva is solid in his defense.
Tossed up on off. Joshua Da Silva gets forward to defend it.
Slightly shorter on off. Mayers blocks it off the back foot.
Slower through the air on off. Mayers blocks it out.
Tossed up nicely on middle. Mayers works it to mid-wicket this time.
A fuller delivery on middle. Mayers works it to mid on.
On middle and Mayers blocks it out.
Tossed up on off. Mayers tries to defend but gets an inside edge onto his pads.
Shorter in length and turning into the batter. Joshua Da Silva goes back and defends it.
Fuller delivery on middle. Joshua Da Silva blocks it out.
Joshua Da Silva is the new batter. West Indies lead by 14 runs.

OUT! LBW! Mehidy Hasan strikes in his first over after Tea. Just what Bangladesh needed and Jermaine Blackwood, who was looking so good before Tea, departs early in this session. This is flatter and slightly shorter on middle. Jermaine Blackwood goes back and looks to work it towards the leg side. However, he misses it and the ball hits his pads. There is a huge appeal and the umpire raises his finger. Blackwood reviews it. The UltraEdge shows no bat involved and the Ball Tracking shows that it is hitting the stumps. The century stand is broken.

On middle and flatter. Jermaine Blackwood with a front-foot defense.
Pitches it on off and it turns back in slightly. Mayers defends it off the inside half of his blade towards the leg side.
Shakib is not ready to give any flight and bowls it flatter again on off. Mayers defends it off the front foot.
Pushes it quicker, around off again. Mayers is ready to defend it yet again.
Hasan with a flatter delivery on off again. Mayers with a solid block.
Shakib goes fuller on off. Mayers gets well forward and defends it.
A flatter one and slightly shorter on off, Mayers goes back and blocks it.

Welcome back, folks! It is time for the final session of the day and Bangladesh players make their way out to the middle now. Kyle Mayers and Jermaine Blackwood are also out there to resume their innings. Shakib Al Hasan will start with the ball. Here we go...
… DAY 2, SESSION 3 …

Bangladesh, on the other hand, would be disappointed with how things panned out in the afternoon session. They had momentum on their side coming into this session but gave away too many loose deliveries early in the session and that allowed the Windies batters to get their confidence back. Both the current batters are naturally aggressive and if Bangladesh don't get their act right in the final session, things can drift away from them quite quickly. We will be back for the final session of the day at 12.30 am IST (7 pm GMT, the previous day). Stay tuned.

A fantastic session for the home team! Just what the doctor ordered for them after a mini-collapse of sorts at the backend of the first session. They have scored 111 runs in this session and have taken a lead of 14 runs now. This century stand between Mayers and Blackwood has surely brought West Indies back in control of this game. Mayers was the aggressor between the two and took some risks early on. However, he eventually settled in quite nicely and both these batters are looking set for a big one here.
Slightly short, around off and spinning in, Jermaine Blackwood goes back and helps it towards mid-wicket. That will be Tea on Day 2.
Loopy and full, around off, Blackwood leans forward and defends it to the off side.
Flighted and on middle, turning away with some extra bounce, Mayers controls well and guides it towards point for one.
Around leg, Mayers helps it off the inner half to square leg.
Fuller and around leg, Mayers pushes it back towards the bowler.
Flighted and on middle, Blackwood eases it down to mid on and scampers across to the other end.
Shortish and on off, punched from the back foot to covers.
Around middle, flatter and shorter, it's worked in front of square leg for one.

What was that? Shakib attempts to dig it in short, but he drops that in his own half. The ball reaches the batter on a couple of bounces. It's going down, Blackwood tries to slog but misses. It's called a no ball.
Flatter and shorter on off, blocked from the back foot.
Quicker this time, around off and skidding in, Blackwood goes back and defends.
Loopy around off, another defensive shot off the front foot by Jermaine.
Flighted and full, around off, it's defended off the front foot to covers.
Shakib Al Hasan comes back into the attack.
Around off, flatter through the air, Mayers defends it back watchfully.
Flatter and shorter, around off, Mayers moves inside the crease and strokes it through covers. Two more.
Tossed up, around off, defended off the front foot to the off side.
Slower through the air, full and flighted outside off, Blackwood latches onto it and drives it through covers. Khaled uses his right boot to stop the ball and saves one run.
Fires it full and on middle, it's defended back.
Turning down the leg side, Blackwood lets it be.
Overpitches outside off, Mayers leans forward and drills his drive to the left of the deep point fielder. A brace is taken. 12 from the over, West Indies lead by 5 runs.
FOUR! BANG! West Indies move into the lead. Short in length and around off, Kyle Mayers hangs on the back foot and whacks it to the cover region for a cracking boundary.
Fuller and around middle, some late swing into the batter, Mayers defends it back to the bowler.
Short and around leg, some uncomfortable extra bounce, Blackwood jumps and glances it down to long leg for a single.
CENTURY STAND! Back of a length, around off, Mayers punches it firmly through point for a single. A very important partnership between the two!
FOUR! The fielder in the deep fails to pick it. Short in length and outside off, Mayers camps back and slaps it over backward point for a boundary. Fifty for Mayers, his third in Tests.
Streaky! Loopy delivery, full and around leg, Blackwood kneels down to sweep but it takes the top edge and runs towards fine leg. The batters get two and the deficit now is just 7 runs.
Full and flighted outside off, Mayers drives it down to long off for a single.
A half-tracker outside off, Mayers cuts it through point for a brace.
Slider around off, defended off the front foot.
Flatter and shorter outside off, left alone.
Short and wide outside off, Mayers leaves it alone.
Drifting down the leg side, a touch short in length, Blackwood tries his best to glance but misses.
Bouncer on middle, JB ducks.
EDGY FOUR! Another well-directed short ball, around middle and leg, Jermaine Blackwood takes on the challenge to pull but it takes his gloves and flies behind the keeper for a boundary.
Extra bounce from a good length around off, Blackwood rises on the back foot to defend but it takes the inner edge and goes on one bounce over the stumps.
Back of a length, around off, Jermaine Blackwood remains on the back foot and works it through mid-wicket for two.
The batter has just blocked that from his crease.
Ebadot Hossain (14-6-26-0) is back on.
Fullish and sliding down the leg side, it's clipped off the pads by Mayers but he finds the fielder at backward square leg.
Loopy and full, around off, Kyle Mayers defends it near his front pad.
Quicker one, around off, defended off the front foot.
Fires it full and on middle, Mayers does well to defend it back towards the bowler.
Arm ball around off, it's defended off the back foot.
Turn and bounce outside off, Mayers tries to drive but misses.
Short in length and outside off, steered behind point for a single.

Khaled steams in from 'round the wicket and cooks a very sharp bouncer. Around middle, Blackwood ducks at the last moment. Nurul Hasan jumps but fails to stop cleanly. They cross. It's also a no ball as this is the third bouncer over the head of the batter in this over.
Khaled goes length, drops it around off, Jermaine is on the front foot as he defends.
Yet another bouncer, around leg, Blackwood sways away and this time Nurul collects.

Four byes! Plenty of extras going West Indies' way. An attempted bouncer, a slower one, down the leg side, Blackwood leaves and it bounces in front of Nurul Hasan who fails to stop it. A boundary results at fine leg.
Shortish again, outside off, this time, Blackwood hangs on the back foot and plays it down gently to point.
Khaled hurls across a half-tracker on off, some steep bounce there, Jermaine Blackwood goes on his back foot, jumps and defends it down.
Almost drags it on! Mehidy Hasan serves a slider around off, short in length and skidding into the batter, Mayers goes back to punch but gets an inside edge onto the pads.
Fuller this time, it's fired around middle and off, Mayers drives it towards the cover fielder.
Quicker one, a slider on off, Mayers goes on the back foot and blocks.
Tossed up, around off, defended back to the bowler.
Turning down the leg side, it's worked behind square leg for a run.
A dipping full toss on middle, it's pushed to mid off.
Mehidy Hasan (13-2-42-1) is back into the attack now.
Bangs it in short, around middle and leg, Jermaine Blackwood stands across and pulls it down to fine leg for one.
Around off, on a length, Blackwood keeps his weight on the back foot and punches it to covers.
Serves it on a length and around off, Jermaine Blackwood defends it off the front foot to mid on.
Digs it in short, wide outside off, Jermaine goes on his toes and cuts but fails to beat the diving point fielder.
Fuller and around off, Mayers plays it down with soft hands to point and collects a single.
Khaled cooks a bouncer around off at 128 kph, and Mayers sways away from the line.
Flatter around the pads, defended on the leg side.

FOUR! Slapped! Shakib drags his length short and delivers it outside off, Jermaine Blackwood goes deep inside the crease and smashes it through cover-point. Chase is on as Mehidy Hasan runs after it but fails to pull it back in. Could have done better.
Slower through the air, full and around off, Jermaine Blackwood pushes it to cover-point.
Flighted and full outside off, Blackwood drives it to mid off.
Short and wide outside off, Blackwood tries to cut but misses. The keeper appeals but nothing from the umpire.
Around middle, on a shortish length, Mayers turns it through square leg for a single.
Short and outside off, some extra bounce, Blackwood leaps on the back foot and defends it down on the surface.
Fullish and outside off, Jermaine Blackwood drives it powerfully towards mid off but fails to beat the fielder.
Lands it on a length and close to off, Jermaine Blackwood defends it close to his front off, off the inner edge.
Fiery delivery, short and sliding down the leg side, Jermaine Blackwood tries glancing it off his hips but then pulls his bat back.
Pitches it up and outside off, Mayers crunches his drive through cover-point and takes a single.
Lands it full and on middle, Mayers defends it close to his front pad. The bowler appeals for an lbw, thinking it was pad first but nothing from the umpire.
200 up for West Indies! They trail by just 34 runs now! Fuller delivery on the pads. Mayers flicks it to deep square leg for a single.
Pitches on middle and turns into Mayers. He works it towards the leg side.
On the shorter side, outside off. Jermaine Blackwood punches it to sweeper cover for a single.
On middle and fuller. Jermaine Blackwood defends it calmly again.
Slower through the air on middle. Jermaine Blackwood defends it towards the leg side.
Pitches it on off and it turns into middle and leg. Kyle Mayers works it to deep square leg for a single.
Khaled Ahmed delivers it on a length and down the leg side. Jermaine Blackwood looks to flick it but does not connect.
Lands on a length, on off. Jermaine Blackwood drives it back to the bowler.
Goes fuller on off. Jermaine Blackwood drives it to mid off.

Goes fuller on off. Jermaine Blackwood drives it back to the bowler. Khaled Ahmed gets a fingertip to it as he tries to stop it in his follow-through. The ball goes on to hit the stumps at the bowler's end. There is an appeal for run out but Mayers is well inside his crease.
On a length, on off. Jermaine Blackwood works it to short mid-wicket.
Shortish length, outside off. Mayers rides the bounce and punches it to sweeper cover for a single.

Drinks break. A steady hour after Lunch for West Indies to bring back some sanity into their innings. It's been a good partnership between Jermaine Blackwood and Kyle Mayers in which the latter has shown more intent and looked to take a few risks as well. The deficit is now down to 38 runs and Bangladesh will be hoping for a wicket or two after this break to stay in the hunt.
Shakib goes fuller on off. Jermaine Blackwood is solid in his front-foot defense.
Angles into leg. Mayers tries to clip it but misses. The ball brushes his pads and goes towards short fine leg. A leg bye is taken.
Shakib keeps it a tad short again but closer to off and Mayers defends it off the back foot.
FOUR! Boundaries continue to flow! Short and wide outside off. Mayers cuts it and gets it in the gap through backward point for a boundary.
Shakib Al Hasan is continuing with a flatter trajectory here, on off and Mayers blocks it out.
A flatter one, around off. Mayers defends it towards the off side.
FOUR! Beautifully played! Khaled Ahmed goes a tad short outside off. Jermaine Blackwood waits for the ball to come, rides the bounce and then punches it through backward point for a boundary.
Goes fuller on off, Jermaine Blackwood drives but straight back to the bowler.
Lands on a length, on middle. Jermaine Blackwood nudges it to the leg side.
Slightly shorter again, around off. Jermaine Blackwood punches it to point.
Goes a tad fuller on off. Jermaine Blackwood pushes it towards covers this time.
Starts the new spell with a back-of-a-length delivery on off, Jermaine Blackwood defends it off the back foot.
Khaled Ahmed (12-1-41-2) returns to have another burst.
This is another flatter one from Shakib, angling into middle, Mayers goes back and defends it.
Again fires it fuller but down the leg side. Mayers tries to clip it but misses. Nurul Hasan dives and collects the ball in the second attempt, thinks about appealing but there was no bat.
Drifts on the pads. Mayers clips it to square leg.
It is short and around off again. Mayers punches it to mid off.
On the shorter side again, on off. Mayers defends it nicely again.
A flatter and shorter delivery on off. Mayers blocks it out.
Shakib Al Hasan brings himself into the attack for the first time on Day 2. 0 for 9 in his 2 overs so far.
A fullish delivery, outside off. Jermaine Blackwood leaves it alone.

Bit of misunderstanding between the batters but no damage is done in the end! Fullish delivery on off. Jermaine Blackwood drives it to mid off. Mayers, at the non-striker's end, wants a single but is sent back in time by Blackwood.
Lands on a length, on off. Jermaine Blackwood blocks it off the front foot.
Back of a length, around off. Mayers guides it through backward point for a single.
Islam responds with a bouncer on off. Mayers sways away from the line of the ball.

Hasan bowls closer to the off pole and Jermaine Blackwood is ready with his defensive block.
Short and wide outside off. Jermaine Blackwood cuts it to the point fielder.
Goes slightly shorter on off. Jermaine Blackwood uses the depth of the crease and defends it.
Pushes it quicker again on off. Jermaine Blackwood with a solid block again.
Goes quicker and flatter on off. Jermaine Blackwood defends it from his crease.

FOUR! Fifty partnership comes up with that boundary! Hasan drifts on the pads. Jermaine Blackwood sweeps and sweeps it fine. The ball races away towards the fine leg fence. West Indies trail by 52 runs.
Goes a tad fuller on off. Mayers drives but finds the fielder at short cover.
A length delivery on off. Mayers defends it with the middle of his blade.

Excellent delivery! Gets some good bounce this time. Lands on a length, around off. It bounces sharply and beats Mayers who tries to push it away. The bowler appeals but he himself is not convinced. The finger stays down and Shakib looks away.
Same length, around off. Maybe a tad short and Mayers pushes it towards point as he opens the face of his blade.
Serves a length delivery again, around off. Mayers gets a good stride forward and pushes it towards covers.
Lands on a length, on off. Mayers blocks it solidly from his crease.
FOUR! Nicely played! This is fuller on the pads. Jermaine Blackwood kneels and sweeps it through the backward square leg region for a boundary.
Goes flatter and quicker on middle. Jermaine Blackwood defends it nicely again.
Pitches on middle from 'round the wicket. It turns into Jermaine Blackwood a bit as he goes back and blocks it.
Flatter delivery on off. Jermaine Blackwood is solid in his defense.
On middle and pitched up this time. Jermaine Blackwood works it to mid-wicket.
Slower through the air, on middle. Jermaine Blackwood defends it back to the bowler.
FOUR! Another short ball and this time Mayers hammers it away! Short and around off. Mayers is into the position early and pulls it towards the mid-wicket fence for a boundary.
Islam follows a yorker with a bouncer. On middle and Mayers ducks under it.
Good yorker this time on middle. However, Mayers also does well to get his bat down in time.
Back of a length, on off, Mayers punches it through cover-point for a couple of runs.

FOUR! In that gap again, the second slip is wide than usual and the ball runs away through that gap for a boundary. Lands on a good length, outside off. A full delivery on middle. Mayers pushes it to mid on.
Loopy and full, around off, Jermaine Blackwood defends it by striding forward. 7 from the over, West Indies trail by 70 runs.
Flighted and full, outside off, Mayers drives it through mid off and collects a single. Hit a maximum to force the field back and then collect a single, smart!
Quicker delivery, around middle and leg, helped to mid-wicket.
Flatter and on off, short in length, Mayers punches but finds the fielder at cover-point.

Full and around off, Mayers strides forward and defends it to the off side.
Fullish and around off, Jermaine Blackwood forces it back towards the bowler who fails to collect it and deflects it to mid on. Maiden.
Fuller in length and outside off, Blackwood plants his front foot forward and then makes a leave.
In the zone around off, on a length and angling away, Blackwood covers his stumps and shoulders arms.
Wayward delivery, on a good length and down the leg side, Blackwood tries to buy some cheap runs but fails to connect with his attempted flick shot.
On a length again, around middle and leg, Blackwood defends it down from the back foot.
Angling across the batter, on a good length outside off, Jermaine Blackwood allows it through.
Shoriful Islam (10-4-34-1) is back into the attack.
Drifting down the leg side, Kyle eases it off his pads but finds the fielder at backward square leg.
Keeps it full and around leg, Mayers drills it down the ground but finds mid on.
Fires it in, flat and short around off, Kyle Mayers defends it from the back foot.
Slower through the air, full and on off, turning in, Blackwood fails to flick and it goes off his pads, past short leg. They cross for a leg bye.
Tossed up, full and on off, Jermaine defends it back towards the bowler.
Loopy delivery, landing full and outside off, Mayers drives it with gentle hands through covers and picks up a single.
Around off on a length, the batter has just watchfully blocked this out.
Again the length is on the shorter side, around off, Blackwood defends it with his elbow pointing skyward.
Shortish and wide outside off, Jermaine Blackwood defends it from the back foot to the off side.
Fuller in length, around off, Blackwood pushes it firmly to mid off.
Fraction short and on off, Jermaine Blackwood defends it solidly from the back foot.

Four leg byes! West Indies continue to get some bonus runs here. Back of a length, around middle and leg with extra bounce, Blackwood tries to glance but misses. It kisses his thigh pad and screams away to the fine leg fence.
Floated and full, around middle and skidding in, Mayers leans forward to defend but gets an inside edge. It goes to short leg.
Fuller and around off, Blackwood knocks it down to mid on and races across to the other end.
FOUR! Risky attempt from Blackwood there as he was a long way across the stumps. Spinning down the leg side, Jermaine gets a faint tickle behind the ball as it races down to fine leg. 150 comes up!
Slower through the air, short and on off, Jermaine defends it down from the back foot.
Shorter on off, Blackwood goes back and turns it to mid-wicket.
Full and floated on off, defended back.

FOUR! Risky shot! Kyle Mayers continues to take risks. Short in length and outside off, Mayers reaches out for it as he throws the bat through the line. It takes the outside edge and flies down to third man for a boundary.

Four leg byes! Valuable runs for the home team. Sliding down the leg side, on a length from 'round the wicket, Mayers tries to flick but misses. It brushes his pads and scoots away to the fine leg fence.
Shortish and on off, Mayers swivels on the back foot with his pull shot but only manages to drag it off the bottom edge to mid on. Kyle is living dangerously at the moment.
Uppish! Back of a length, outside off, and holding off the surface, Mayers stands back and plays a mistimed pull shot. It flies over the bowler and the mid on fielder cuts it off.
Another play and a miss! It seems that Kyle Mayers will bat his way. Short in length and wide outside off, Mayers tries to cut away from his body and misses.
Swing and a miss! Short in length and outside off, keeping low, Kyle Mayers is early into his cross-batted shot and misses. He needs to be careful with his shot selection on this tricky surface.
Flatter and quicker on middle, a bit on the shorter side, Jermaine Blackwood moves inside the crease and blocks it down.
Floated and full around off, Jermaine presses forward and defends it on the leg side.
Leans forward to a full ball and defends it down.
Very full this time, around off, Jermaine drives it back towards the bowler. He fails to stop cleanly and it goes on to hit the stumps at the non-striker's end.
Slightly short and on middle, Blackwood flicks it off his pads but finds the short leg fielder.
Fuller in length and around off, Mayers drives it wide of the cover fielder and picks up a single.
Mehidy Hasan to start from the other end. He got a big wicket of Kraigg Brathwaite in the first session, can he get another one early after Lunch?
In the channel outside off, Jermaine Blackwood shoulders arms to end the over.

Shortish and around off, Blackwood gets across and works it towards short leg. The fielder there doesn't get down in time but does well to stick his right foot out and deflects it towards square leg. Prevents at least a run with his smartness.
Again there is plenty of inward movement behind this good-length delivery, Jermaine Blackwood flicks it to mid-wicket.
Around off, on a length, shaping in, Jermaine defends it to covers.
Better from Ebadot. Delivers it on a good length outside off and gets it to curl back in a long way, Blackwood defends it from the back foot.
Ebadot begins the afternoon session with a wayward short delivery, down the leg side, Blackwood leaves it alone.

Welcome back to the afternoon session! Bangladesh players are in a huddle and after some last minute tips from Shakib Al Hasan, they disperse to take their respective positions. Jermaine Blackwood and Kyle Mayers also march out to resume their innings. Ebadot Hossain will start with the ball for Bangladesh. Here we go...
… DAY 2, SESSION 2 …

West Indies, on the other hand, would be wondering how they messed things up in the session where they were motoring along quite nicely. Campbell departed after another fine knock and after that, the skipper, Brathwaite and Reifer steadied the ship for the Windies. However, just when it was looking like West Indies will go through this session without further damage, the backbone of the West Indian batting line-up, Brathwaite was clean bowled. Suddenly panic kicked in as Reifer departed in the very next over and Bonner too did not last long. West Indies still trail by 97 and we surely have an interesting game on the cards, folks! Do join us for the afternoon session at 10.10 pm IST (4.40 pm GMT).

What a comeback this has been from Bangladesh! They looked down and out for the most part of the session with nothing much happening for the bowlers but Mehidy Hasan got rid of Brathwaite and that triggered a collapse as Bangladesh eventually managed to take four wickets in the morning session. Have to say, the session has belonged to Bangladesh. They got just a solitary wicket in the first hour of play after Campbell and Brathwaite put together a century stand. However, some brilliant bowling by Mehidy and Khaled Ahmed in the last phase of this session brought life to Bangladesh's bowling effort.

FOUR! Plays late and finds the boundary on the last ball of the session. Short in length, around off and skidding in, Kyle Mayers camps back and punches it behind square on the off side for a boundary. That will be Lunch on Day 2.
Slower through the air, full and around off, Kyle lunges and blocks.
Quicker and around off, skidding in, Mayers is solid as he draws forward in defense.
Loopy and full, around middle, Mayers defends it from the inner half to mid-wicket.
Flighted and full, around off, Mayers drives well but finds mid off.
Slider, around off and skidding in, Kyle Mayers defends it from the front foot.
Delivers it on a good length around off, from wide of the crease, Blackwood is on the back foot as he defends it down safely.
Goes full this time to surprise the batter, around off, Jermaine is expecting it and defends it quite easily.
Keeps bowling short. It's around off, Jermaine Blackwood punches it from the back foot to covers.
Shortish again, around off and jumping onto the batter, Blackwood gets on the back foot and defends it on the leg side with little discomfort.
Back of a length, around off at 132 kph, Blackwood stays on the back foot and defends it down.
Short in length but down the leg side, Jermaine Blackwood sways away from the line. It dies down on its way to the keeper.
Loopy and full, around off, Jermaine nudges it behind square leg and picks up a single.
Quicker and in the line of the stumps, Blackwood goes back and defends it from the toe end of his bat.
Lunges to meet a full ball around off and defends it safely.
Slight inward spin on this delivery along with some extra bounce, Jermaine Blackwood goes on the back foot as he defends it down.
Flatter and close to off, defended off the back foot.
The batter has just watchfully blocked this out.
Kyle Mayers is the next man in.

OUT! SOUND OF TIMBER! Khaled Ahmed is a rhythm bowler and he is in a fantastic rhythm at the moment. Serves a shortish ball around off, plenty of energy again as he hits the deck hard and gets the ball to change its line after pitching. It hurries onto the batter, Nkrumah Bonner is on his toes to defend but all he manages is an inside edge and it rattles the stumps behind. Two wickets in the over and the hosts are pinned on the back foot at the stroke of Lunch.
Commentary.Howout: b Khaled Ahmed

Commentary.Commentary: Serves it on a good length and around off, Nkrumah Bonner gets on the front foot with an angled bat and taps it down to gully.
Khaled Ahmed aims for the blockhole but it turns out to be a low full toss on middle, Jermaine Blackwood does well to keep it out safely in the gap at square leg. They cross for a run.
Khaled Ahmed has a spring in his stride now. Delivers it short and close to off, it's a good leave from Blackwood.
Huge shout for a caught behind, not given. Plenty of energy on this delivery. A touch short and around off, nipping away a bit, Jermaine Blackwood stands back to push inside the line but misses.
Jermaine Blackwood walks in next to steady the shaky ship of West Indies. Two new batters at the crease and Bangladesh would love one more wicket before Lunch.

OUT! BOWLED! Raymon Reifer departs now and two wickets in successive overs for Bangladesh. This dismissal is quite similar to the one of Shakib Al Hasan on Day 1. Bangladesh are clawing their way back in this game now. Khaled Ahmed keeps it short and it is around off. Raymon Reifer looks to guide it square of the wicket on the off side but gets an inside edge of his blade and it goes on to shatter the stumps. Raymon Reifer departs after getting a good start and he will be disappointed here.
Commentary.Howout: b Khaled Ahmed

Commentary.Commentary: Beats the outside edge again! It is that drift from Mehidy Hasan again. He lands it around off and Bonner looks to defend it off the front foot. However, the ball beats the outside edge of his blade.
A flatter one on off. Bonner defends it off the front foot.
Flighted and around off, Bonner is squared up in defense as he keeps it out on the leg side.
Fuller and quicker around leg, defended out to mid-wicket.
Shortish and on middle, Bonner goes on his toes and plays it down the leg side.
Nkrumah Bonner walks in next. West Indies trail by 103 runs.

OUT! BOWLED! Ohh... Mehidy Hasan strikes and gets a big, big wicket of Kraigg Brathwaite! Mehidy Hasan has a happy knack of providing breakthroughs when the chips are down and he does that yet again! This one is nicely tossed up in the air, it drifts around middle and off as Kraigg Brathwaite lunges to defend the trajectory of the ball. But it lands and straightens to beat the outside edge and goes on to strike the stumps. Kraigg Brathwaite is completely bamboozled.
Commentary.Howout: b Mehidy Hasan

Commentary.Commentary: On a length, outside off. Kraigg Brathwaite pushes it gently through the point region for a single.
Angles a length delivery into middle, Raymon Reifer nudges it to the left of the square leg fielder and takes a single.
Shortish length, outside off. Raymon Reifer leaves it alone.

Once again the hoop is out to check the shape of the ball. This is the third time Bangladesh have complained and they are third time lucky. The umpires have asked for the replacement as the ball got stuck in the hoop and didn't pass the test.
On a length, on off. Raymon Reifer blocks it out.
This is very full, on off. Raymon Reifer digs it out to the cover region.

Again that low bounce, Raymon Reifer needs to be careful here! Back of a length and angling into off from 'round the wicket. Raymon Reifer looks to defend but gets rapped up on the pads. There is an appeal but no damage done. Maybe, the impact was an issue.
Too full in length, around off, Kraigg Brathwaite hits it down the ground but finds the mid on fielder.
Leans forward and defends a full ball to covers.
A fuller delivery on middle. Raymon Reifer nudges it past short leg for a single.

FIFTY for Kraigg Brathwaite! Another one for this prolific opening batter, his 27th in Test cricket, 5th against Bangladesh. He missed out on a century in the first game and would be looking to make a big one here. Slightly shorter outside off. Kraigg Brathwaite waits for it and guides it wide of first slip. He runs three and gets to his fifty.
A flatter delivery on off. Kraigg Brathwaite blocks it out.
Nice slower loopy delivery on off. Kraigg Brathwaite defends it off the outside half of his blade towards the off side.
Bangs it short, around off. Raymon Reifer sways away from the line of the ball.
Goes fuller on off. Raymon Reifer drives but finds the fielder at covers.
On a length, outside off. Raymon Reifer leaves it alone.

An appeal for a caught behind but it has gone off the thigh pad to the keeper. Lands a length delivery but drifts it down the leg side. Raymon Reifer looks to clip it but misses. The ball goes to the keeper. An appeal for a caught behind but the umpire is not interested and Shakib takes a wise decision to not review it.
A fuller delivery on off. Raymon Reifer drives it to mid off.

FOUR! Finds the edge but the ball goes in that gap between first slip and widish second slip. A good-length delivery, around off. Raymon Reifer looks to defend it off the front foot. He gets a good healthy outside edge but there is no conventional second slip in place and the ball goes through that region for a boundary.
Again there is an issue reported by Bangladesh. They are not happy with the shape of the ball. The umpires though feel that it's in good enough shape to continue...

This time he gets a run! A fullish delivery, around off. Raymon Reifer drives it to the right of the mid off fielder and sets off for a single. A bit risky run but Raymon Reifer makes it safely in the end.
Drifting on the pads this time. Raymon Reifer turns it towards the leg side but no single for the left-hander.
A flatter and fuller one on off. Raymon Reifer pushes it towards the off side.
Pushes it quicker on leg at 84 kph. Raymon Reifer defends it off the front foot. Some excitement there for the Bangladesh players as he does not defend it with the middle of his blade.
Shorter and outside off. Kraigg Brathwaite cuts it to sweeper cover for a single.
Tossed up from Hasan on middle. Kraigg Brathwaite leans forward and pushes it towards the leg side.
That keeps a bit low! Angles a length delivery from round the wicket, on off, Raymon Reifer defends it off the bottom of his blade.
Goes fuller on off. Raymon Reifer drives it through covers and comes back for the second run.
Pulls his length back and gets some good bounce. However, it is outside off and Raymon Reifer makes an easy leave.
Serves a length delivery, outside off. Raymon Reifer leaves it alone.
Good delivery! Pitches it on a good length and angles it in from 'round the wicket. It is around off. Raymon Reifer presses forward to defend but the ball beats the outside edge of his blade.
On a length, around off. Raymon Reifer leaves it alone.
Pushes it quicker and outside off. Kraigg Brathwaite lets it go.
Tossed up on off. Kraigg Brathwaite with a front-foot defense.

Slows his pace and pulls the length back slightly, on middle at 80 kph, Kraigg Brathwaite goes forward to defend but then adjusts his defensive shot as the ball bounces a bit extra. It rolls towards square leg.
Quicker and flatter at 87 kph on middle, Kraigg Brathwaite defends it off the front foot again.
This is a bit slower in the air, on off again and Kraigg Brathwaite blocks it off the front foot.
Fuller delivery on off. Kraigg Brathwaite drives it to covers.
Spin for the first time this morning, Mehidy Hasan is getting ready to bowl. He bowled just one over last evening and went for 9 runs.

FOUR! In the air...but wide of the fielder at gully! Khaled Ahmed, after bowling a few length deliveries, goes fuller outside off. Raymon Reifer goes for a big drive. However, he gets a thick outside edge and the ball goes past the diving gully fielder for a boundary.
This is good from Khaled Ahmed! Lands it on a good length again and around off. Raymon Reifer makes another good leave.
Keeps it in that channel, around off. Raymon Reifer with another leave.
Lands on a length, outside off. Raymon Reifer leaves it alone.
Goes fuller on middle. Raymon Reifer drives it to the right of mid on. However, Shakib Al Hasan dives across and makes a good partial stop. Two runs are taken.
Khaled Ahmed starts his new spell with a back-of-a-length delivery around off. Raymon Reifer punches it to the cover-point fielder.

DRINKS! Bangladesh have broken the opening stand in the last hour but not before they have taken West Indies to a very strong position. Kraigg Brathwaite is looking quite solid in the middle and this is a big chance for Reifer to make this opportunity count. Shoriful has provided the breakthrough for Bangladesh and with this pitch offering some uneven bounce, bowling in the line of the stumps could be a way forward for the Bangladeshi bowlers. They have been much better with their control this morning but they need wickets to put some pressure back on the Windies. Khaled Ahmed returns to bowl after the break.

Fuller in length, around off, Reifer caresses it past the bowler and the mid off fielder gets across to stop it with a dive. He fails to do so cleanly but manages to take some pace off it. The ball slows down as it approaches the fence and by the time it is retrieved by the same mid off fielder, the batters take three runs.
Shortish and on off, defended from the back foot to the off side.

Shoriful goes short on this occasion, around off, Raymon Reifer tries to defend from the back foot but the bounce keeps on getting big on him, beats his bat and strikes him on the stomach area. Raymon shows no pain.
Shoriful delivers it on a length around off, shaping in, Reifer defends it from the inner half to square leg.
In the channel outside off, it's left alone.

FOUR! Raymon Reifer opens his account with a convincing boundary. Fuller in length around off, angling in, Raymon gets forward and across with a straight bat and drives it crisply past the bowler for a boundary down the ground.
Beaten! Ebadot Hossain puts it on a length and around off, straightening off the seam again, Kraigg Brathwaite sticks back to defend but it whistles past the outside edge. Another maiden.
Around middle, on a length, Brathwaite pushes it towards mid on.
Edgy! Ebadot Hossain serves it on a good length and close to off, Kraigg Brathwaite is on the back foot in defense. But the ball straightens to catch the outside edge and goes on one bounce to gully.
Action replay of the previous delivery, another bouncer around leg but this time at 137 kph, Kraigg Brathwaite sits underneath it.
A bumper at 130 kph, down the leg side, Kraigg Brathwaite ducks underneath it.
Shortish and on middle, Brathwaite stands back and wrists it behind, towards the leg gully fielder.
Fuller and on off, it's driven firmly back towards the bowler who makes a fine stop. Maiden.
Lands it on a good length and around off, Raymon Reifer leans forward and defends it to covers.
On a driving length outside off, Raymon Reifer walks across the stumps a bit and then makes a leave.
Zippy delivery, a touch short in length and outside off, Raymon leaves it alone. The keeper has to stretch to his right to collect the ball as there was some late movement.
On a length and outside off, Raymon Reifer allows it through to the keeper.
Fuller and on off, Raymon Reifer tries to defend off the front foot but his bat turns in his hands and the inside edge takes the ball rolling to mid-wicket.
Fullish and on middle, Brathwaite flicks it with the angle but finds mid on.
We are witnessing some indifferent bounce at the moment. A bouncer around off, not rising much, Kraigg Brathwaite crouches and allows it through. The ball goes on one bounce to the keeper.
Fuller in length and outside off, it's pushed off the front foot to covers.
On middle, a length ball, defended to mid on.

FOUR! Well played! This one is on a length and around off, Kraigg Brathwaite hangs on the back foot and plays it down with an angled bat. It runs away wide of the gully fielder and finds the fence at third man.
Extra bounce is turning out to be a nuisance for the batters. A touch short and around off, Kraigg Brathwaite is taken by surprise and fends it away somehow at the very end.
Raymon Reifer walks in at number 3.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! Shoriful Islam strikes and the extra bounce has brought John Campbell's downfall. It's banged in short, around middle and leg, John Campbell stands back to ride the bounce as he aims to pull it through square leg. But the extra lift on this delivery beats his bat and kisses his gloves on its way to the keeper. Nurul Hasan catches the ball and jumps in delight. John Campbell walks. Can Bangladesh build on this breakthrough? West Indies trail by 134 runs.
Commentary.Howout: c Nurul Hasan b Shoriful Islam

Commentary.Commentary: Delivers it on a good length around off, John Campbell flicks it to the left of mid-wicket and turns down the single as the fielder quickly gets to the ball.
Inswinger from a length around off, Campbell defends it in front of his front pad.
On a length and outside off, angling in, John covers his stumps and shoulders arms. Low bounce on this occasion.

Serves it on a length around off, some extra bounce, Campbell gets forward and across and helps it from the inner half of his blade. It rolls through square leg and they collect a couple of runs. 100 comes up for West Indies!
Shoriful comes from 'round the wicket and angles in a length ball around off, Brathwaite works it wide of mid on and takes a single.
Slips a full ball down the leg side, Campbell tries to flick but misses. Nurul Hasan has to dive across to his right to secure the ball. Good effort.
Delivers it a shade full and around off, angling away, John Campbell watchfully lets it go.
Lands it on a length and outside off, John Campbell winds up for a booming drive but it hits him high on the bat and rolls to mid off. Called a no ball for overstepping.
Extra bounce again, from a length around middle and leg, Brathwaite tries to work it across the line but misses. It goes off his pads to square leg and they steal a leg bye.
Fullish and outside off, Brathwaite defends it off his front foot, back towards the bowler.
On a length around off, shaping in, Kraigg pushes it away with an angled bat and places it to the right of the point fielder.
Very wide outside off, short in length, Kraigg Brathwaite doesn't go chasing after it.

A muted appeal for an lbw. Shoriful Islam gets some extra bounce on this delivery as he lands it on a good length outside off. John Campbell tries to work it on the leg side but misses and is rapped high on the pads. The appeal is not entertained.
This one is on a good length and outside off, shaping in a shade, John Campbell defends it watchfully by shuffling a bit across the stumps.
Fuller this time, around middle, Kraigg helps it to the right of the mid on fielder and rotates the strike. Smart batting.

FOUR! Kraigg Brathwaite is trying to score off every loose delivery and that's a big change in his approach. A little bit of width outside off, Brathwaite camps back to ride the bounce and smacks it through covers.
Identical to the last delivery but this time the ball skids on with the angle, rather than moving off the seam. Around off and Kraigg punches it from the back foot to covers.
Beats the bat with his first ball of the day. An outswinger, landing on a length around off, Kraigg Brathwaite stays on the back foot to defend but is beaten on the outside edge.
Shoriful Islam (6-3-19-0) is back into the attack.
Short and wide outside off, shaping away, John Campbell tries to cut but misses.
Sliding down the leg side, Campbell fails to neatly tuck it off his pads.
The batter has just blocked that from his crease.
FOUR! Good shot! Too full in length, around off, John Campbell doesn't try to hit it hard, just shows the full face of his bat and caresses it down through mid on for a boundary.
Outside off, left alone. It's called a no ball for overstepping.
Straighter in line, Campbell uses the angle and clips it through square leg for a couple of runs.
Slants in a length, around off and angling in, John Campbell shows the full face of his bat and blocks it back towards the bowler.

FOUR! Glorious from Kraigg Brathwaite. He has shown a lot of intent in this knock, contrary to the one in Antigua. Fuller in length and wide outside off, Brathwaite leans forward and strokes it elegantly through covers.
Full and around off, defended strongly to covers.
In the zone outside off, skidding off the surface, Kraigg leaves.
Four leg byes! Back of a length, around middle and leg, Kraigg Brathwaite fails to glance it around the corner and it goes off his thigh pad to the fine leg fence.
Fuller and it's darted in on off, Brathwaite presents a straight bat as he blocks it back.
Bowls it on a good length and outside off, Kraigg shoulders arms.
Lands it on a length, outside off and holding its line, John Campbell makes a watchful leave.
Fuller and on off, again Campbell mistimes his drive back to the bowler.
Movement into the batter, from a good length outside off and stays low a bit, Campbell does well to keep his eyes on the ball as he defends it to mid-wicket.
Serves it on a length and outside off, John Campbell covers his stumps and shoulders arms.
Keeps it very full and close to off, John Campbell mistimes his drive off the bottom half and the ball rolls back to the bowler.

Speedy delivery, full and around middle, angling down, Kraigg Brathwaite tries to flick but misses. It goes off his pads to leg gully where the fielder dives but fails to make a clean stop. They cross for a leg bye.

On a length, around off. Kraigg Brathwaite defends it towards point. The fielder at point collects it and fires a direct hit at the batter's end. Not sure why he did that, Kraigg Brathwaite was well inside his crease. The ball deflects off the stumps behind square on the leg side and a single is taken.
Bowls it on a length again but this time on the off-stump line. Kraigg Brathwaite blocks it off the back foot.
Lands on a length, outside off. Kraigg Brathwaite leaves it alone.
Beaten! Khaled Ahmed keeps it a tad short, outside off. Kraigg Brathwaite looks to push it away from his body. The ball though seams away a bit and beats the outside edge of his blade.
Back of a length, on off. Kraigg Brathwaite defends it calmly towards the off side again.
Khaled Ahmed with a length delivery on off. Kraigg Brathwaite is solid in defense.
Fuller length, on off. John Campbell drives it straight to mid off.
Pulls his length back a bit and bowls on the off pole line. John Campbell defends it towards point.
Angles it on leg again. John Campbell is ready to flick it but misses. He gets hit on the pads and there is a slight appeal but it is clearly going down leg.
Goes fuller and drifts on the pads. John Campbell flicks it through square leg for a couple.
On a length, angling into middle, John Campbell defends it towards the leg side.

Loose shot from John Campbell! This is on a length, outside off. John Campbell goes for a big expensive drive away from his body and the ball seams away just a tad to beat the outside edge of his blade.
On the shorter side, on off. Kraigg Brathwaite blocks it off the back foot.
Nicely played! Short and wide outside off. John Campbell punches it through covers and the batters run three. The Bangladesh bowlers need to be tighter with their lines.
Back of a length, angling into off. There is a bit of extra bounce and John Campbell defends it onto the turf with his one hand off the handle.
Keeps it a tad short again and gets a good bounce off the surface. It is outside off though and John Campbell leaves it.
Shortish length and outside off. John Campbell cuts it to the point fielder.
On a length, on middle. Kraigg Brathwaite works it to fine leg for a single.
Khaled Ahmed to start from the other end.
This is straighter again angling into the pads. John Campbell flicks it but finds the square leg fielder this time.
Goes fuller and into middle and leg. John Campbell clips it to mid-wicket.
On a length and bit closer to the off pole. John Campbell initially sets up to play this one but then lets it go.
Serves a fullish delivery, outside off. John Campbell with another leave.
On a length and wider outside off. John Campbell goes chasing for it but misses.
Ebadot Hossain lands it on a good length and outside off. John Campbell leaves it alone.

We are all set for Day 2, folks! The Bangladesh players make their way out to the middle. The two overnight batters for West Indies, John Campbell and Kraigg Brathwaite also make their way into the middle. It will be Ebadot Hossain to start with the ball for Bangladesh. Here we go...

PITCH REPORT - Samuel Badree and Stacy-Ann King are down for the Pitch Report. Badree says some of the cracks opened up a little bit more and it might help bowlers today. King adds that there was more movement for the bowlers in Antigua. Badree concludes by informing that straighter lines brought rewards for the bowlers on Day 1 and that will be the game plan for the bowlers to bowl straight, wicket to wicket line.

As we wait eagerly for the action to unfold on Day 2 in St Lucia, across the Atlantic ocean, England and New Zealand are fighting it out in what is turning out to be a fascinating Test match at Headingley. England took the lead of 31 runs at the end of their first innings as they stitched together another breathtaking fightback to end with 360 after being restricted to 55/6. The Black Caps currently have 9 wickets in hand and have a lead of 21 runs, we are surely set for an exciting finish in that game. In this game too, West Indies batted quite positively on Day 1 scoring at a run rate of over 4, we are surely moving into a new era of Test cricket and let’s hope we have a quality day of Test cricket here at Gros Islet, St. Lucia.

The lead for Bangladesh is still 167 but West Indies have all 10 wickets in hand, courtesy of a splendid opening stand between Kraigg Brathwaite and John Campbell in the final session of the first day. Both of them looked quite comfortable in the middle and Bangladesh have a tough task ahead after they failed to put up a formidable first-innings total. Still, a lot of cricket to play though and if Bangladesh bowlers can get some early wickets in the morning session, things can change around quite quickly. Can the Bangla Tigers roar back into this game? Or will West Indies build on the good work they did on Day 1? A crucial first session coming up.

Hello and a very warm welcome to Day 2 of the second Test match between West Indies and Bangladesh. Day 1 provided us with some engrossing cricket with Bangladesh starting off the day with a much better application with the bat than they did in the first Test. However, as the day progressed, West Indies lifted their game and are now in a position to dominate if they continue to bat the way they did in the final session of Day 1.
… DAY 2, SESSION 1 …

Bangladesh would be gutted by the fact that they have missed out on a golden opportunity to get a formidable score in the first innings after setting a platform for the same in the morning session. Tamim Iqbal was quite positive at the top of the order and Mahmudul Hasan Joy too gave him good company. However, from 105-2, Bangladesh crumbled to 165-7 and it was only because of the effort of Litton Das and some handy runs from the tailenders that Bangladesh got to a respectable total, though it looks below-par after the way West Indies have batted so far. The Bangladesh bowlers, much like their Windies counterparts, have been guilty of bowling way too many boundary balls. They needed someone to get a big hundred but that did not happen and it is upto their bowlers now to bring them back in this game. We will be back with our coverage on Day 2 and the first ball will be bowled at 7.30 pm IST (2 pm GMT). Our build-up though begins a lot earlier. So do join us for the same. Cheers!

James Siddons, the batting coach of Bangladesh, comes up for a quick chat. Says that they were a lot more patient and left the balls well. Adds that West Indies bowled well but Bangladesh didn't bat for long. Mentions that they need to bat longer and they are failing to do that. Tells that Litton Das and Tamim Iqbal looked fantastic but need to score big runs. Smiles and adds that a couple of umpiring decisions didn't go their way. Further says that there was no swing and admits that it's not a 234 pitch. He is happy though with the opening stand but is disappointed that they fell short of a good total.

The pitch at St. Lucia was expected to assist the pacers but surprisingly it has not been as helpful to the pacers as expected. The Windies bowlers in search of that magic deliveries ended up bowling way too many boundary deliveries and though they pulled things back a bit with two wickets in that first session, overall the bowling was not upto the mark. However, there was still enough to trouble the batters if the bowlers managed to hit good lengths consistently and that is what the hosts did in the second and third sessions and that brought wickets at regular intervals. Credit should be given to Anderson Philip, the man on his Test debut who provided the breakthroughs when his team needed it the most, breaking a solid opening partnership first and then getting rid of Anamul Haque to trigger a collapse of sorts. Other bowlers too chipped in though the boundary balls also kept coming every now and then and Bangladesh eventually managed to cross 200.

A commanding performance from the home team in the final session! West Indies have started off solidly with the bat and the openers have brought the deficit down to 167 after bundling out Bangladesh for 234 earlier in the evening session. Have to say, West Indies have bagged this first day of play and would be looking to cash in with the bat on what looks like a very good batting strip. Bangladesh, on the other hand, started the day on a positive note but in Test cricket, you need to keep the intensity going over a long period of time and that is where Bangladesh lacked and gave away the advantage they gained after the morning session.

Tossed up and outside off, left alone.

Flighted and on middle, it's flicked behind square leg for a run.

Mehidy Hasan is into the attack now.
Sliding down the leg side, it's eased away behind square leg for one.
Fullish and on off, angling in, Campbell gets forward and strokes it to short cover.
Spears it in, very full and on middle, Brathwaite clips it down to fine leg for a single.
Outside off, an easy leave for the home captain.
Shortish and outside off, pushed with an angled bat through point for a single.
Almost drags it on. Ebadot angles in a length ball around off, John stays back to defend but gets a bottom edge. It almost squeezes through his legs. Saved by the left foot.
Floated and on middle, drifting in, Kraigg leans forward and defends it down.
Arm ball around off, skidding in, KB defends it from the inner half to short leg.
Loopy and full around off, it's defended back.
FOUR! Smashed! Overpitched by Shakib, around middle, Kraigg Brathwaite clears his front leg and drills it down to long on for a boundary. 50 up fo West Indies!
Slower through the air, full and around off, Brathwaite defends it off the front foot.
Too full in length around middle, Campbell knocks it down to long on and takes a single.
Full and outside off, pushed to point to complete the over.
In the zone outside off, on a good length, Brathwaite allows it through to the keeper.

Short in length and outside off, John Campbell camps back and steers it through backward point. Anamul races across to his right and dives to stop the ball near the fence. Saves two runs for his team.
Slants in a length ball around off, from 'round the wicket, it's blocked from the back foot.
Extra bounce there, from a good length around middle and leg, Kraigg tries to glance but it takes the thigh pad and runs down to fine leg. They cross.
Starts his spell with a length ball outside off, shaping away, Kraigg shoulders arms.

Pushes it quicker through the air again, around middle, Campbell defends it from the crease.
Flighted and around middle, John leans across the flicks it off his pads to short mid-wicket.
That is punched off the back foot, but straight towards the bowler.
Quicker and around off, defended from the back foot.
FOUR! Too full in length and outside off, Campbell is on the front foot as he drives it crisply through covers for a boundary.
Loopy and around off, John Campbell walks down the track and defends it back.
Shakib Al Hasan comes into the attack.
Ends the over with a short delivery on middle. John Campbell pulls it to deep square leg for a single.
Angling this length delivery on middle from 'round the wicket. Kraigg Brathwaite clips it to square leg for a single.
On a length, around off. Kraigg Brathwaite leaves it alone.
FOUR! Sixth boundary of this innings and we are just into the 7th over here! A half-volley around off. Kraigg Brathwaite drives it beautifully through covers for a boundary.
Lands on a length, on off. Kraigg Brathwaite blocks it solidly off the front foot.
On a length, angling into leg. John Campbell clips it to fine leg for a single.

FOUR! Khaled Ahmed has been pretty poor with this new ball! Overpitched around off. Kraigg Brathwaite leans forward and creams it through covers for a boundary.
On a length, outside off. Kraigg Brathwaite leaves it alone.
Full again. On middle and John Campbell flicks it to deep square leg for a single.
This is full and way down the leg side. John Campbell looks to flick it but misses.

On a length, outside off. Kraigg Brathwaite leaves it.
On a length, on middle. Kraigg Brathwaite tucks it to square leg.

Well bowled! Again that angle that takes the ball away from the right-hander brings Kraigg Brathwaite in some trouble. Lands on a good length, around off. Kraigg Brathwaite looks to defend but the ball goes away with the angle and beats the outside edge of his blade.
Lands on a length and angles it across the batter. Kraigg Brathwaite makes a good leave.
Shoriful Islam continues with a fullish length, on off. Kraigg Brathwaite drives it to mid off.
Lands on a length and it is quite wide outside off. John Campbell keeps his bat close to his body and leaves it.
This is full and around off. John Campbell mistimes his drive back to the bowler. Actually, it goes off the inside half of his blade to the bowler.
Goes fuller on middle. Kraigg Brathwaite clips it to deep square leg and gets a single.
On a length angling into leg. John Campbell works it to deep backward square leg for a single.

On a length, angling into middle at 128 kph. John Campbell blocks it onto the turf.

Pitches it up and outside off, Brathwaite shows no intention to play at it.

Coming to the ball - It is a back-of-a-length delivery angling into middle and leg from 'round the wicket angle. John Campbell looks to clip it but misses. On a length, angling into middle. Kraigg Brathwaite works it towards the leg side for a single.
Back of a length, angling into middle. Kraigg Brathwaite pushes it towards mid on.
FOUR! Good timing from the Windies skipper! Back of a length, outside off. Kraigg Brathwaite rides the bounce and punches it through covers for a boundary.
Lands on a length and drifts down the leg side again. Kraigg Brathwaite is happy to let it go.
A fullish delivery but down the leg side. Kraigg Brathwaite lets it go.

On a length, outside off. John Campbell mocks a swipe across the line after the ball passes him.
FOUR! Another boundary! Shoriful Islam continues with that fullish length, outside off. John Campbell drives and does that a bit uppishly but wide of the point fielder for a boundary.
FOUR! Nicely played, John Campbell gets off the mark with a boundary! Fullish delivery on off. John Campbell drives it past mid off for a boundary.

Right then, a spirited display from Nurul Hasan but his fine knock of 60* can only help Bangladesh achieve a lead of 12 runs but they have managed to avoid an innings defeat. West Indies bowlers were on the mark and Kemar Roach, Alzarri Joseph and Jayden Seales all ended with three wickets each. They were aggressive this morning and have bundled out the opposition in a hurry. Just 13 runs needed then for the hosts to win the match and clean sweep the Test series 2-0. It is now a question of how much time will their batters take to finish the job. Join us in a bit as the run chase is coming up next.

OUT! RUN OUT! Bangladesh are bundled out. A length ball, outside off. Hasan drops it to point. Ahmed looks for a quick single as it was the last ball but it didn't travel much away as John Campbell collects the ball at point and scores a direct-hit at the bowler's end. West Indies were confident and the replay confirms that Ahmed is well short. Not what Hasan would have hoped for but it was a tough task for him with the tail-enders on the other side. Bangladesh are all out on 186.

Short ball, around odd. Hasan steps across and ducks under it. He will look to take a single now.
This is way outside off and on the shorter side. Hasan throws his bat at it but fails to connect.
Fuller and on off. Hasan lofts it over the bowler's head and to long on but again keeps the strike.
On a length and wide of off. Hasan keeps it out.
No ball! Seales sees Hasan shuffle across and he bowls way outside off. Outside the pitch and a no ball is called.
A fuller ball, outside off, nipping away. Hasan has a big swing across but misses.
Fuller and on off. Ahmed solidly defends it.
Short in length and on middle, pulled to deep square leg for a single. Ahmed needs to survive one ball.
Joseph keeps the same length and Hasan works it straight down to long on. No run taken.
SIX! What a shot! Short again but Hasan anticipates the length and stays back to pummel it over deep mid-wicket for a biggie.

FOUR! Bangladesh in the lead now! A very hard fought fifty for Nurul Hasan! He is fighting hard! Back of a length and around off. Hasan shuffles across and cuts it to deep point. The fielder runs to his right but fails to cut it off.
A short ball, slightly down the leg side. Hasan fails to pull it away.
Length and outside off. Ahmed easily leaves it. Nurul Hasan will breathe a sigh of relief.
A fuller ball, outside off. Ahmed looks to defend but gets a thick outside edge and it falls short of the fielder near the gully region.

OUT! LBW! Islam goes now and Seales gets a seond wicket in the over! A slower ball, too full and angling around middle and leg. Islam fails to work it away and the ball goes under his bat and hits him on the pads. A huge shout for LBW and up goes the finger. However, Islam takes a review. Looks straight there. Ultra Edge shows no bat. Ball Tracking shows three reds and Bangladesh lose their 9th wicket.

Commentary.Commentary: Five wides! Too short this time, following the batter on the leg side. Islam leaves it. Joshua Da Silva fails to get a hand to it and it goes behind to the fence. Bangladesh have now wiped off the deficit completely and the scores are level.
Short of a length and around leg. Islam makes room and looks to pull but misses.

OUT! TAKEN! Bangladesh are 8 down now! West Indies inching closer to the win! A well-directed short ball on middle. It lobs over short leg but Raymon Reifer does well to run back and dive down to his left to take a sharp catch. Bangladesh trail by 5 runs.

Length ball, outside off. Hasan slaps it to deep point. This time he doesn't take a single.
Short again on middle. Hasan makes room and upper cuts it to the right of third man for a couple of runs. Good fielding there.

In the air but falls safe! Short of a length and on off. Hasan looks to pull but gets a top edge and it falls safely in the square leg region. No run taken.

A single taken! Short of a length and outside off. Hasan cuts it behind square on the off side for a single. Hossain has to watchout the last ball.
FOUR! Bangladesh now trail by 16 runs! A slower full ball, angling on middle. Hasan smashes it straight down the ground for a boundary.
Short again but this is outside off. Hasan looks to cut but misses.
SIX! He will look to cut the deficit single-handedly! Short of a length and on middle. Hasan hangs back and pulls it to deep mid-wicket for a biggie.

Bangladesh simply do not seem to be learning from their mistakes. After a spirited showing with the ball early on Day 3, Khaled Ahmed was able to pick up his maiden five-wicket haul in Test cricket and helped his team clean up the opposition tail. The visitors did have a big lead to get rid of but a few loose shots at the wrong moments have cost them dearly. Najmul Hossain Shanto got well-set and just gave it away before the skipper, Shakib Al Hasan too was dismissed, leaving the tail well exposed. Can Bangladesh somehow manage to get through the first session without losing a wicket? Or will West Indies be able to get those remaining 4 wickets in a hurry? We'll find out soon.

West Indies came into Day 3 in a strong position but the tail wasn't able to hang on for too long and Kyle Mayers was the only one who mustered up some runs before getting out on 148. They did get bundled out for 408 but still had a substantial lead of 174 runs. When the hosts came out to bowl, it was yet again Kemar Roach who made the new ball talk and snatched up a couple of early wickets. Things became a bit slow in the middle but Alzarri Joseph came back with fire in his belly and late in the evening picked up a couple of wickets to make sure West Indies ended the day well ahead of the game.

Hello folks! A very warm welcome to Day 4 of the second Test match between West Indies and Bangladesh. The visitors still trail by 42 runs with 4 wickets in hand and the hosts certainly seem to be in a great position to seal the series 2-0. There was a lot of rain on Day 3 and that meant we lost more than an entire session's worth of play. Hopefully, Day 4 stays rain-free and the match can go on smoothly.

Right then, Bangladesh still trail by 42 runs and have just 4 wickets in hand. West Indies will be sniffing a clean sweep here and would want to finish off the game in the first session on Day 4 itself.
