Or will the hosts make light work of the Bangladeshi tail? Find out on Day 4. Do join us early for the build-up as well. Till then, take care and goodbye!

The batting woes continue for Bangladesh, more than skill it is the lack of a proper shot selection that puts them in precarious positions such as the one they are in at the moment. Khaled Ahmed, Shoriful Islam and Mehidy Hasan all starred with the ball on Day 3 and it was Ahmed whose hard work paid off as he picked up a maiden five-wicket haul in Test cricket. Trailing by 174 runs when they came out to bat, Bangladesh yet again lost wickets early in the innings and even though Najmul Hossain Shanto did manage to do a bit of repair work alongside skipper Shakib Al Hasan, Shanto too gave into temptation. With just one recognized batting pair left at the crease, the visitors need to do well to not lose by an innings. They certainly need a miracle here.

West Indies mustered up a substantial lead of 174 runs and with the overcast conditions, they certainly got extra help while bowling. Almost an entire session was lost due to rain after about one hour of play in the morning but once play resumed, Kemar Roach was in the zone and got early breakthroughs for his side. He went past the 250-wicket mark in Test cricket, surpassing Michael Holding in the process as well. The Windies pacers faced a bit of a resistance from the opposition but Alzarri Joseph bowled a fiery spell towards the end of the day which brought him a couple of wickets and has put West Indies in pole position of winning the game.

Day 3 is generally known as the moving day in a Test match but it has been a bit of a stop-start day here. The game however has moved along nicely and is nearing its final stages. West Indies started the day in a good position and even though they couldn't muster up as many runs as they would have liked, they did get past the 400-run mark, something that they haven't done on this ground since 2008, thanks to a big ton from Kyle Mayers. The Bangladeshi bowlers were good on Day 3 and did manage to bundle out the opposition fairly soon.

The players are going off! The groundsmen have been on their toes for the last few minutes and it has gotten really dark now. The umpires have a chat and signal for the players to go off. This might be the last bit of play for the day it seems as the West Indies players can be seen shaking hands with each other. The live pictures from the ground depict that there is heavy rain at the moment and even the groundsmen are struggling to keep a hold of the covers. The official word is that it will be Stumps on Day 3!
Joseph keeps it a bit on the shorter side and pushes it wide this time. Mehidy Hasan leaves it alone.
And again! Short and over middle, Mehidy Hasan does well to evade the line of the ball.
Banged in short and over off stump, Mehidy Hasan sways away from the line of the ball.
Short of a good length, on off. Mehidy blocks it off.
Back of a length, there's some width on offer. Nurul stays on the back foot and punches it sweetly through covers for three runs.
On a good length, on off. Nurul Hasan has an uncharacteristic swipe across the line but misses and gets hit on the right arm.
This is outside off, it is left alone easily.
On a length and on off. Mehidy stays back on his back foot to block it.
Back of a length and outside off. Mehidy looks to cut but misses.
Fuller and outside off. Mehidy defends on the front foot.
Angling on middle, tucked to mid-wicket for a single.
FOUR! A gentle half-volley, on middle. Nurul chips it wide of mid on and to the deep mid-wicket fence.
Short in length and slanting on middle. Mehidy fends it away on the leg side.
Wide! Length ball, way outside off. Mehidy leaves it alone. A wide given.
Length ball, around off. Mehidy defends it solidly.
Full and on off. Mehidy prods and defends.
This is positive aggression from Alzarri Joseph! Short of a length and just outside off. Mehidy feels for it as he tries to push but misses.
Five wides! This is too short and on middle. Mehidy sits and Joshua Da Silva cannot do much about it as well. It rolls behind and into the fence.
Length and on off. Blocked out.
Mehidy Hasan walks in with Bangladesh in a spot of real bother.

OUT! EDGED AND GONE! Alzarri Joseph hydrates himself and gets the big wicket of Shakib Al Hasan! With that the hopes of Bangladesh getting dull as well! Another shot from a Bangladeshi batter which could have been avoided! This is on a length and outside off, it nips away off the deck. Shakib Al Hasan has a poke at it but gets an outside edge to second slip where John Campbell tries to take it but he fumbles and the ball hits him on his chest and lobs over his head kindly as he takes it on the second attempt.
Commentary.Howout: c John Campbell b Alzarri Joseph

Commentary.Commentary: DRINKS! With just one hour remaining in the day's play, the players take a breather. It is also getting darker by the minute as more and more grey clouds appear. West Indies are in total control of the match at the moment and one more wicket here in the next few overs might all but secure victory for them. Shakib Al Hasan is still out there but needs a world of support from Nurul Hasan to make the opposition bat again.
Length ball, outside off. Nurul plays a back foot punch but straight to point.
On a length and outside off. Nurul hits it through covers for a couple of runs.
Length ball, drifting outside off. Shakib waits and dabs it to the gully region. Good call from Nurul for a single as he was running on the danger side.
A length ball on middle. Nurul wrists it to square leg for a single.
Touch fuller, outside off. Shakib drives it to deep point for a single.
A length ball, outside off. Shakib pushes to the right of covers. He wants a single but is denied by Nurul and rightly so.
Kemar Roach (8-1-22-3) is back on. Also, the ground staff are once again bracing themselves around the boundary ropes, so there might be a bit of rain around the corner. Hopefully not though.
Short ball, outside off. Nurul looks to pull as he tries to ride but gets a bottom edge to the keeper. Joseph and Nurul exchange some words in the end.
Length ball, outside off. Nurul strokes it through covers for a couple of runs.
On off, kept out.
Bangs a bouncer on middle. Nurul sits under it. Excellent from Joshua Da Silva to get a hand to it and save a certain boundary.

What a ripper from Joseph! He is certainly breathing fire now! A sharp bouncer, around off, extra bounce. Nurul stands tall and is late to react to this short ball. The ball found the edge and lobs on the leg side. There is no one at short leg and it falls safely.
Angling on the pads, Shakib tucks behind square on the leg side for one more.
Outside off, length, Nurul punches it to covers for a couple of runs.
A length ball, around off, nips in. Shakib flicks it to square leg for a single.
No ball! Another short ball, outside off. Shakib leaves it and questions how many more to the umpire. A no ball signaled for height.
West Indies are serving only bouncers to Shakib! Another one outside off. Shakib tries to pull but it was too far for him.
Length ball, outside off. Nurul punches with hard hands through covers for a single.
Length and on middle, pulled to deep square leg for a single.
West Indies are not allowing any room for comfort! A bouncer on middle. Al Hasan ducks under it.
Nurul Hasan comes in

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! Najmul Hossain Shanto just couldn't resist the temptation and he will be mightily disappointed with his shot selection. This is full and wide, enticing the batter to go for the drive and Shanto goes for the expansive cover drive. Shanto's feet though go nowhere and the outside edge is found. Easy catch behind the sticks for Joshua Da Silva and Alzarri Joseph strikes after probing away for a bit. Shanto departs in the 40s and Bangladesh still trail by 70 runs.
Commentary.Howout: c Joshua Da Silva b Alzarri Joseph

Commentary.Commentary: Length this time, around middle and off. This is kept out by Shanto.
Uppish but in the gap! Full again, angling into middle and leg, Najmul Hossain Shanto looks to flick but does so aerially through the vacant mid-wicket region for a brace.
Goes fuller this time, Shanto blocks it off.
Back of a length, on middle. Shanto keeps it out.

Bye! Alzarri Joseph is certainly extracting a bit extra from the surface at the moment. Banged in halfway down the track and around off, the ball just takes off and goes past Shakib's outside edge. Joshua Da Silva leaps up but fumbles and the batters are able to cross over.
On a fuller length and around off, punched towards mid off.

FOUR! Edged away! Length ball, outside off, Najmul Hossain Shanto plays at it with soft hands and gets an outside edge through the vacant gully region for a boundary. The 100 is up for Bangladesh and they now trail by 73 runs.
Banged in over middle and leg, Shanto ducks under it.
Back of a length, this is defended off the back foot.
The length is dragged back a bit this time, on middle. Shanto with another solid defensive shot.
Pitches it up and angles it into off stump. Najmul Hossain Shanto solidly blocks it off the front foot.
Back of a length, around off. This is dabbed down towards backward point. Maiden!
At the moment, it's trial via short ball for Shakib Al Hasan. Pacy bumper, over leg stump. Shakib takes his eyes off the ball as he looks to take it on and gets comprehensively beaten.
On a good length, around middle and leg. Shakib manages to defend it out.
Pitches it up a bit, around middle, Shakib blocks it out.
Another bouncer! This time again over middle but bouncing high and that allows Shakib to duck under it.

Well, that had some serious heat behind it! Banged in short and over middle, at 143 clicks. The ball just zips through and Shakib Al Hasan does extremely well to get his head out of the line of the ball.
Back of a length and over middle, Shanto hops on the back foot to keep it out.
Pitched up, outside off, this is driven through cover-point for a single.
Good length, on off and there's a bit of variable bounce again. Shakib manages to keep it out.
Almost gets chopped on! Length ball, around off, Shakib looks to cut from close to the body but gets an inside edge past the stumps.
Good comeback delivery from Anderson Phillip! This is a bouncer, angled into the body and rises at a good height. Shakib Al Hasan looks to take on the hook shot but pulls out of it and rightly so.
FOUR! Up and away, intentional from Shakib. This is on the shorter side and well outside off, Shakib throws his hands at it and gets it over backward point for a boundary.
This is banged in short and over middle stump, Shanto ducks under it. Maiden!
Well bowled! Length, but gets it in that channel around off and the ball just takes off. Najmul Hossain Shanto has a slight dab at it but gets beaten for pace.
On a good length, around off. Shanto taps it towards cover and Shakib wants a single but it's a firm call of no from Shanto.
Short again but once again down the leg side, easily left alone by Shanto.
Good length, on leg stump, this is tucked away towards mid-wicket.
Starts off with a pacy short ball, at 141 clicks and down leg. Najmul Hossain Shanto sits under it comfortably.
Alzarri Joseph (4-0-17-0) is back for his second spell.

Four byes! This one shoots up like a rocket! Angling a length ball, around off, the ball hits the crack and climbs past Al Hasan who evades quickly and even Joshua Da Silva is taken by surprise. A boundary.
Outside off, pushed to covers.
A length ball, outside off, Shanto dabs it through gully for one more.
A length ball, outside off, jagging in. Shanto shoulders arms to it.
FOUR! Shanto was standing out of his crease so the keeper stands up! This is short and Shanto cuts it uppishly and over point for a boundary.
A length ball, on off. Al Hasan knocks it to point for a single.

Shakib Al Hasan seems to be in a bit of pain here. That last delivery from Jayden Seales pinged him on one of his fingers on the bottom hand and that can be really painful. The physio is out and having a look. Shakib gets his finger strapped and he is good to go.
Short of a length and on middle. Al Hasan fends it away awkwardly to square leg for a single.
A full ball, this one swings back in sharply from outside off. Al Hasan looks to defend but gets an inside edge onto the pads.
Half-tracker, on middle. Shanto gets on top of it as he pulls it to deep mid-wicket. Three runs this time.
Extra bounce this time, length and on middle. Shanto keeps it out.

Short in length and slanting on the hips. Shanto is rushed as he looks to tuck it away but misses and the ball brushes his thigh pad before going into the mitts of Joshua Da Silva. An appeal for it but the umpire shakes his head. UltraEdge confirms no bat there.
Length ball, around off, shaping in. Al Hasan hangs back and flicks it in front of square on the leg side for a single.
Full and just outside off. Shanto defends it to cover-point.
FOUR! This time Najmul Hossain Shanto was ready to play the short one as he gets on top of the bounce and pulls it to deep square leg for a boundary.
Short of a length and on off. Shanto anticipated that a bouncer was incoming and he ducks under it.
Full and on off. Blocked out.
Length ball, outside off, nipping slightly in. Shanto thinks to play at it but withdraws his bat quickly.
On a length and outside off. Al Hasan drops it to point for a single.

There is a slight drizzle which isn't too bad but the umpires look at the ground staff waiting for their signal. For now, play can go on but if gets any heavier than this, there might be yet another delay as the ground staff stay on their toes waiting patiently around the boundary ropes. There is still sunshine, so it might only be a passing drizzle.
Outside off, on a length. Shanto leaves it alone.
A bouncer now, it climbs more. Shanto sits under it.
A yorker now, widish one. Shanto jams it out on the off side.
Superb delivery! This one straightens up off the deck, on a length and on leg. Shanto fails to play it out and gets hit high on the pads.
Four byes! This is full and sliding down the leg side. Shanto misses his flick and it goes past the keeper and to the fine leg fence.
Short of a length and outside off. Shakib tries to cut on the up but mistimes it to point for a single.

DRINKS! Bangladesh still trail by 107 runs and they have 6 wickets in hand. Kemar Roach has been brilliant up front once again but there have been a few loose shots from the batters as well. Right now, there are a few dark clouds hovering around the ground but the sun is still out which is a good sign. It remains to be seen, as to how Bangladesh will negate the opposition bowlers and if they can go into Day 4 without losing more than half their side.
Touch fuller and on middle, eased to mid on.
FOUR! Carbon copy by Shanto! Fuller again, around off. Shanto drives it past the non-strikers end stumps and to long on for a boundary.
FOUR! Too full and on off. Shanto on drives it to long on for a boundary.

Good delivery! A length ball, nipping back in from around off. Shanto is squared up as he looks to defend and he manages an outside edge to the right of third slip where Nkrumah Bonner dives low to his right to collect on a bounce.
Fuller and outside off. Shakib punches it through point for a single.
Leg bye! Short of a length, angling on the hips. Shanto misses his tuck and gets hit on the body. It rolls to square leg for a leg bye.
Jayden Seales welcomes Shakib Al Hasan to the crease with a sharp bouncer. This is bowled from around the wicket and angled in over leg stump. Shakib does well to duck under it.
Shakib Al Hasan walks out to the middle.

OUT! LBW! Jayden Seales finds the right length this time and gets the ball to nip back in sharply from around the off stump. Litton Das is caught on the crease as he looks to play it on the leg side and the ball crashes into his pads, staying a bit low as well. A huge appeal for LBW but it is turned down! After a bit of a discussion, Kraigg Brathwaite does go for the review. UltraEdge shows that there's no bat involved and Ball Tracking comes up with three reds as the ball is going on to hit leg stump. Brilliant review from West Indies and they have the fourth wicket now.
Commentary.Howout: lbw b Jayden Seales

Commentary.Commentary: Just a tad shorter in length and around off. Das shoulders his arms at it.
FOUR! Full and drifting onto the pads, Litton Das clips it off his legs and past square leg for a boundary. Bangladesh now trail by 117 runs.
A slight halt in play as Litton Das wants to change his bat.

Half an appeal from the bowler for LBW but it seems too high. Good length again, around off and just nipping in a touch. Das looks to defend off the front foot but misses and gets struck on the pads. The replay shows that the ball was going well over the stumps.
Good length, around middle and leg. Litton Das goes on the front foot and presents a dead bat at it.
Fuller and angling into middle, this one keeps a touch low. Shanto works it towards wide mid on.
Mayers angles it in from around the wicket and keeps it close to the off pole. Najmul Hossain Shanto makes a watchful leave.
Risky single but it's well run in the end. Just short of a length and around off, Das drops it towards cover and sets off for a quick run.
On off, Das stays solid in defense.
Mayers pushes it a bit wider and looks to swing it back in but Das just leaves it alone.
Goes a bit fuller and bowls it on the fourth stump line. Litton Das lets it through to the keeper.
Good length, on the fourth stump line, Shanto leaves it alone. Another maiden over for Jayden Seales and West Indies.
Fuller in length and outside off, Najmul Hossain Shanto looks to cover drive but ends up dragging it towards mid on.
Around the top of off, blocked out by Shanto.
Pitched up on off, this is driven towards mid on.
This is on a length and outside off, left alone by Shanto.
Full and outside off, just a bit too wide to entice the batter into playing the drive.
On a good length, over middle and leg, Das eases it out towards mid on. Maiden to start with from Kyle Mayers.
Pitched up, on off. Litton Das stays solid in defense.
This is angled in fuller and into off, Das blocks it off the front foot.
Around off, this is guided away towards point.
Scrambled seam this time from Kyle Mayers, on a good length and on off. Das solidly blocks it out.
Once again in the game, there is a bit of a worry about the condition of the ball. Umpire Joel Wilson checks it thoroughly and deems that it is good enough for play.
Starts off with a length, outside off. Easy leave this time around for Litton Das.
Maiden! Close to the off pole and well left by Shanto.
Gets the wide yorker in now, Najmul Hossain Shanto looks to squeeze it out but is beaten for pace.
A touch fuller and on off, Shanto drives it back towards the bowler without any timing.
Nice, probing line from Jayden Seales. Length again, angling in from outside off but the ball holds its line. Shanto makes the leave at the last second.
A bit of a yes and no but no harm done. This is around off, Shanto taps it towards cover and looks for a single but sends his partner back in time.
Seales comes from around the wicket and serves a length ball around off. Shanto keeps it out on the off side.
Ends with a lovely delivery! A fuller ball, outside off. Das looks to drive it but misses.
Length and outside off, nips in. Das looks to drive but mistimes it to mid-wicket. This is good from Roach.
Tad full and around middle and off. Das blocks it out on the leg side.
Hard length ball, outside off. Das lets it go.
Fullish delivery, wide of off. Das drives it through covers for a brace.
A fuller ball, swinging in around off, Das pushes it to mid on.
Length ball, outside off. Shanto strokes it to covers.
On a length and just outside off. Blocked to covers.
Another outside off delivery. Shanto shoulders arms.
Length and outside off. Left alone.
On a length and on middle at 132 kph. Das turns it to square leg where the fielder dives to his right and stops it. One. 50 up...
FOUR! Very full and tailing on the pads. Das helps it away to fine leg for a boundary.
Jayden Seales is brought into the attack now.

A huge, huge appeal for LBW but not given! West Indies do not review as well! They think height might be an issue! Roach slants a full ball, around middle and leg, there is steep bounce as well. Shanto looks to flick it but misses and gets hit on the pads. Ball Tracking later shows wickets were missing.
Length ball, just around off, jags back in. Shanto is hurried as he blocks it out.
On off, kept out.
Full and angling on middle. Das tries to flick it away but inner edges it behind square leg for a single.
Tight from Roach! Slants a length ball on middle. Das is solid as he defends this.
Length and outside off. Left alone.
Overpitched and outside off. Das leans and drives it through covers for three runs as Kraigg Brathwaite chases the ball and saves a single.
Around off on a length. Blocked out.
On the pads, flicked to deep square leg for one.
FOUR! Good shot! A length ball, outside off. Shanto punches it very late and through gully for a boundary.
Dropped! A length ball, around off. Shanto tries to play straight drive but plays it uppishly and back to Phillip but it was too quick for him to show his reflexes.
Length ball, slanting across on off. Shanto taps it to covers and denies a quick single.
Full and outside off, played back to the bowler.
Two runs! A length ball, outside off. Das punches it aerially and past point. The ball does not have legs to run away and the fielder cuts it off near the fence. Two.
Touch fuller and around off. Shanto tucks it off the inner half of the bat and to mid-wicket for a single.
Angles a full ball on middle. Shanto is solid behind the line to defend.
Fuller and on off. Shanto defends it solidly.
A length ball, outside off. Das drops it through covers for a single. He is off the mark.
And again! Fuller and around off, Shanto shoulders his arms. Anderson Phillip starts his spell with a maiden.
Pitched up, in that channel around off. Shanto leaves it alone.
This is pitched up, around off, Shanto drives but straight towards silly mid off.
A touch fuller and on off, solidly defended off the front foot by Shanto.
Length again, on off. Najmul Hossain Shanto taps it towards cover and looks for the quick single but is sent back by his partner.
Starts off with a length ball, around middle. Shanto blocks it out from inside his crease.
Goes fuller and angles it in from outside off. Litton Das plays it with soft hands towards cover-point.
We are back for the final session. West Indies players are ready on the field. Litton Das will join Najmul Hossain Shanto in the middle. Kemar Roach will complete his over.
...Day 3, Session 3...

Update 12.05 am IST (6.35 pm GMT, previous day) - The live visual shows the covers are coming off and the resumption must be just around the corner. Stay tuned. Tea has been taken so the game will resume at 12.30 am IST (7 pm GMT, previous day), if the weather permits. This small session belongs to West Indies and to be precise Kemar Roach who ran through Bangladeshi top order. The visitors need to make sure that they don't lose any more wickets in the final session. Join us in a bit.

The umpire signals out as he rushes off the field because the rain has got heavier and the covers are on. The forecast suggests it will be on and off like this throughout the day. At the moment, the whole ground is not covered so we can anticipate it is a passing shower and hope we resume the innings quickly. Stay tuned for further updates.

OUT! LBW! Kemar Roach serves a length ball and the ball jags back in sharply from around off stump. Anamul Haque looks to work it leg side but misses and gets pinged on the front pad. Joshua Da Silva pouches the ball behind the stumps as well. The appeal though is for LBW and it is given! Anamul Haque reviews it straight away as he thinks it is a bit too high. UltraEdge shows that there's no bat involved and the Ball Tracking shows that the ball is clipping the top of middle and leg. The on-field decision will stay and with that, the rain has gotten heavier. Umpire Joel Wilson raises his finger while rushing back into the dressing room, a sight probably never seen before.
Commentary.Howout: lbw b Kemar Roach

Commentary.Commentary: Length this time, angling into middle and leg, Haque keeps it out.
On a nagging length, around off. Haque leaves it alone and the ball swings in late.
Drizzles have started again!
A touch fuller and on middle, this is flicked away towards mid-wicket for one.
Comes from around the wicket and angles in a short ball at the body. The ball takes off after pitching and Shanto does well to sway away from the line of the ball.
FOUR! Alzarri Joseph is just a bit too full and straight at the moment. On middle and leg, Anamul Haque drives it through wide mid on and picks up yet another boundary.
Length and on the pads, this worked away towards mid-wicket for a single.
Short of a good length, angled across the off stump. Shanto lets it through to the keeper.
A bumper now, well-directed and over leg stump. Najmul Hossain Shanto ducks under it well.
Good length, around middle and leg. Shanto hops and defends it out.
FOUR! Pitched up, around off. Najmul Hossain Shanto drives and drives well, gets it past the man at silly mid on and collects a boundary. Bangladesh now trail by 148 runs.

Too close for comfort! Roach goes a bit wider of the crease and serves a big inswinger. Anamul Haque leaves but the ball just misses the off stump by a couple of inches. End of another successful over from Roach.
Probing line and length from Kemar Roach and he seems to be on song here. In that channel around off and just shaping away a touch. Haque has a poke at it but gets beaten past the outside edge.
Length again, close to the off pole. Anamul Haque makes an assured leave.
Anamul Haque is the new man in.

OUT! TAKEN! Kemar Roach has the last laugh and picks up his second wicket early in the innings. This is on a perfect length, around off. Mahmudul Hasan Joy goes back and across looking to defend but gets the outside edge. Jermaine Blackwood takes a sharp catch at third slip around chest height and West Indies with another fast start here.
Commentary.Howout: c Jermaine Blackwood b Kemar Roach

Commentary.Commentary: FOUR! Three boundaries on the trot now for Bangladesh. A full toss, around off. Mahmudul Hasan Joy drills it past the man at silly mid off and into the fence.
FOUR! A bit too straight on this occasion from Kemar Roach. A half-volley on the pads and this is clipped past square leg for a boundary.
FOUR! Overpitched and punished! Full and around off, Najmul Hossain Shanto with a lovely straight drive back past the bowler and into the long off fence.
Good carry through! On a good length, on the fourth stump line and just zipping past the outside edge of Shanto's willow.
Length again, on off, blocked out.
Almost chops it on! Back of a length, around off. Shanto looks to defend off the back foot but gets a bottom edge back onto the deck. Luckily for him, the ball hits his pads and not the stumps.
Length again, in that channel around off. Najmul Hossain Shanto makes a watchful leave.
A length ball, this is slanted well across the left-hander. Shanto leaves it alone.
On middle, blocked out.
A huge appeal for LBW but that might be just missing the leg pole! A length ball, around middle and it jags back in sharply. Joy is beaten by the seam and gets rapped on the pads.
A length ball, outside off, slightly comes back in. Joy defends off the inner half and on the deck.
This one is at 133 kph, on middle. Joy defends on the back foot. No ball called for overstepping.
Length ball, outside off. Joy blocks it very late and on the off side.
EDGED AND FOUR! A sharp bouncer, slanting around off. Joy is not fully into this shot as he tries to dab it away but gets an outside edge and it lobs over the slip cordon for a boundary.
Length ball, around off. Joy defends to covers on the front foot.
Length ball, going across, outside off. Shanto offers no shot.
A full toss on middle. Shanto flicks it to short leg where Raymon Reifer makes a good stop.
Short in length and angling across. Shanto looks to pull but misses.
Tailing on the pads, it is flicked to deep square leg for a single.
Way outside off, on a length Joy shoulders arms.
Length ball, tailing on the pads. Joy misses his flick and gets hit on the pads. It was going down.
Length and outside off. Left alone.
Another nut from Roach! Angles it full and this one straightens up! it is near around off and Shanto makes a sharp leave.
Najmul Hossain Shanto is in at number 3.

OUT! EDGED AND GONE! 250 wickets for Kemar Roach in Test cricket! Not a good shot from Iqbal though! He could have left it alone! Roach bowls a full ball, angling just outside off and makes it to shape away. Iqbal is tempted for a big-booming drive but gets an outside edge and Joshua Da Silva pouches it. He celebrates with his teammates and waves the ball towards the pavilion.
Commentary.Howout: c Joshua Da Silva b Kemar Roach

Commentary.Commentary: Good delivery but Roach can get tighter! A full ball, outside off and nips away off the deck. Iqbal lets it go.
Short in length and outside off. Iqbal shoulders arms to it.
Outside off, left alone.
Length ball, way outside off. Joy leaves it alone for the keeper to collect.
Short of a length and around off, nips away. Joy taps it to point.
This is way down the leg side. Joy lets it through.
On a length ball, outside off. Iqbal punches it wide of mid off for a single.

Overthrow! A length ball on middle. Iqbal tucks it to mid-wicket and calls for a quick single. He rushes across and the fielder has a shy at the bowler's end but misses. The ball probably brushed Iqbal and goes away for a single.
A length ball, angling across, outside off. Iqbal defends it inside the line and against the angle.
Alzarri Joseph to share the new ball with Kemar Roach.
This one shapes away but the line was outside off. Joy makes an easy leave.
Short of a length and around off. Mahmudul Hasan Joy keeps it out.
A length ball, around off, this one nips back in sharply. Joy hangs back and tucks it to square leg.
Roach steams in and serves a short ball, outside off. Joy watchfully leaves it alone.
A length ball, outside off. Joy steps a bit across and blocks it back to Roach.
Bangladesh and Iqbal are off the mark! A length ball, outside off. Iqbal punches off the back foot to deep point for a single.

Kraigg Brathwaite poses with the trophy and all his teammates join him for a group picture now. That is it from this series, it was a bit one-sided as West Indies were too strong to handle for Bangladesh but they have a chance to showcase their talent as the focus shifts on T20I cricket. The three-match series will start on Saturday, 2nd July at 11 pm IST (5.30 pm GMT). So, do join us early for the build-up. Cheers!

Kraigg Brathwaite, the skipper of West Indies says that the confidence of the guys on the back of the win was already high but the planning and execution were key. He then goes on to applaud the efforts of Kyle Mayers and Jermaine Blackwood and also mentions that the Bangladesh bowlers were pretty good as well. Adds that they want to bat for over a hundred overs and would like more batters to get to a century. Mentions that they need more partnerships and a bit more energy in the field to become better. Adds that all the pacers are pretty good and goes on to speak a few positive words about Roach, Phillip and Mayers. Ends by saying that it's all about attitude and it is not about who you are playing against and is looking forward to the next home red-ball series which is against Australia later in the year.

The skipper of Bangladesh, Shakib Al Hasan says that Test cricket is always difficult but they will take a lot of positives from this tour. Adds that after five months they will play a Test series at home and hence will go back and make a few adjustments. Mentions that their batting is not poor but they just need to concentrate a bit better and he believes that the side can compete with the best teams in the world. Also adds that they have a good string of pace bowlers and Khaled Ahmed did really well to pick up a five-fer which is pretty rare for their pacers but they need to play more as a team. Lastly, he mentions that the T20I and ODI squad will be more competent and hopes to put up a good fight.

Kyle Mayers is the PLAYER OF THE MATCH as well as the PLAYER OF THE SERIES for his all-around performance! Mayers says he just tried to be himself and it worked nicely. Adds that it is one of the best centuries as he wanted to do well in this series. Shares that he tries to make the batter play as much as possible and tries to adapt to the conditions. Tells that he carries the same mindset in all three formats and stays positive. On Kemar Roach, he is a role model as they look upon him. He gives his all and to see him achieve the milestone, Mayers is very happy for him.

West Indies will be high on confidence right now. It was a complete performance from them. The bowlers stepped up when it mattered the most and the batters came in with some crucial knocks to keep the team on top all the time. Recapping how the game went, the hosts after winning the toss and electing to bowl were clinical as they didn't allow many partnerships to grow in the first innings and kept Bangladesh to a bit under-par score of 234. Alzarri Joseph had an impressive outing as he took three wickets while Seales, Phillip and Mayers contributed with a decent spell as well. In reply, West Indies got a blistering start before losing their way in the middle. It was then Mayers and Blackwood who did the repair work and helped West Indies take the lead. Mayers scored a brilliant century in the process and helped the hosts to take a big lead of 174 runs. Later, Bangladesh had a poor start once again with the bat and they never really stood a chance against some fiery spell of bowling from the likes of Roach, Joseph and Seales. Nurul Hasan showed good determination but he ran out of partners and eventually with just 13 runs required to win, West Indies grabbed the series with ease.

Bangladesh have a lot of work to do. No doubt there is tons of skills but some poor shot selection and lack of role knowledge have cost them the series. Their batting woes are a big worry as some of the dismissals have been very soft and tame. The senior players didn't step up and the standards were pretty low for the youngsters. Their bowling was decent with a few good spells from the pacers, especially Khaled Ahmed but a few big partnerships allowed the game to slip away from them. All in all, there is a lot of work to be done on the visitors' side as they look to brush this series away and concentrate on the upcoming white-ball leg of the tour.

West Indies sweep the series 2-0! A win was inevitable for the hosts and the batters had to come out to complete the formalities. A clinical performance overall and they clinch 24 World Test Championship points as well. Day 4 saw rain playing a huge role but it was just delaying the result which was always tilting on the hosts' side.
